title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry mixture, stirring just until moist.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn on wire rack.

title: chipmunk brownies
directions: Combine chopped dates and boiling water.
Cool to room temperature.
Cream shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add to cooled mixture.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Put into jelly roll pan and sprinkle with nuts and mini chips. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: our best gingerbread
directions: Sift flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt onto waxed paper. Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy in a large bowl.
Beat in molasses and egg.
Stir in flour mixture, 1/2 at a time, just until blended.
Beat in hot water until smooth.
Pour into a well greased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertips.
Leave in pan to cool on a wire rack or let cool 10 minutes; then loosen around edges with a knife and turn out onto rack.
Cut into big squares.
Serve warm or cold, plain or with a topper of your choice.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in a bowl or casserole.
Cover with lemon juice and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight, turning chicken periodically.

title: cheesecake to die for
directions: Mix all ingredients in a *LARGE bowl on high speed for 20 minutes.
Line outside of spring form pan with foil to make water tight.
Pour mixture into spring form pan, place into roasting pan with 1 inch water.

title: homemade white bread
directions: Heat milk and butter on medium heat until very warm to touch. Put 2 cups of flour, salt, sugar and yeast in a large mixing bowl; blend well.
When milk is very warm to touch, pour into flour mixture and blend well for 2 minutes, with electric mixer. Gradually add enough flour until dough begins to climb your beaters.
Mix on medium speed for 2 more minutes.
Add 3 cups of flour and mix with a wooden spoon until well blended.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add soup, broth, soy sauce and pepper.
Put chicken in a greased dish; cover with sauce and then sprinkle with noodles and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine green pepper, dried onion, tomato sauce, chili powder and Sweet 'N Low.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add ground chuck and cooked rice to cooked sauce.
Put in glass pie plate.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix the beef, pork, onion, crumbs, parsley, seasoning, egg and milk.
Shape into walnut size balls. Brown in hot oil.
Remove from pan and keep warm. Stir flour, paprika, salt and pepper into fat.
Add water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in sour cream until well blended.
Return meatballs to sauce and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Let dough thaw to room temperature.
On lightly floured board roll dough out to 12 x 16-inch rectangle.
Steam spinach for 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Mix spinach, grated cheese, egg and onion.
Spread mixture over dough, leaving 1-inch margin on each side, roll up tightly in jelly roll fashion.
Spread half of the melted butter in bottom of lightly greased 7 x 11-inch square cake pan or two (8-inch) round cake pans.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese over the butter.
Cut or roll dough into 1-inch slices.
Lace slices, cut side down, in pan allowing room for rolls to rise.
Brush tops of rolls with remaining butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let rise until tripled in size. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Stew onion, pepper, garlic and celery in oleo.
Add shrimp and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and pimentos and cook 5 minutes more.
Soak bread in water and squeeze.
Add to shrimp mixture.
Add rice and parsley.
Pour into greased casserole. Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: *May use blueberry, strawberry or peach pie filling.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in 3 tablespoons butter (do not cook through).
Set aside.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms; saute until tender.
Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce, beef broth and sherry; mix well.
Return beef.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and blend.
Heat 2 minutes; do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: yogurt sauce(yields 1 cup)
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a blender.
Puree.

title: della robbia pot roast
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Brown roast well on both sides. Sprinkle with garlic salt during browning.
Remove from heat.
Add brandy and ignite, spooning liquid over roast until flame dies. Drain pineapple reserving all syrup.
Add syrup to roast along with beef stock base.
Sprinkle with fines herbes.
Add prunes and apricots.
Cover tightly and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours until tender. Blend cornstarch into water.
Stir into pan juices until thickened. Add pineapple slices, walnuts and green onions, spooning gravy over to heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate zucchini and set aside.
Place eggs in a mixing bowl.
Using a rotary beater or an electric mixer, beat eggs until they are thick.
Slowly beat in sugar and oil.
In a separate bowl, sift 3 1/4 cups flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix well.
On low speed add dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with wheat germ and zucchini.

title: holiday banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, water and pudding. Chill for 5 minutes. Beat whipping cream until gets stiff. Fold in the ingredients in whipped cream. Layer pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas until all is gone. Put Cool Whip on top. That is optional.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt butter and flour.
Add rest of the ingredients, except milk and cheese.
When well blended gradually add milk and small chunks of cheese.
Simmer until desired thickness.

title: smoked beef brisket
directions: Place meat in dish and cover with liquid smoke.
Sprinkle celery seed and garlic salt over top.
Cover and marinate overnight.

title: alice's stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown ground meat, onions (tops cut off) and bell peppers. Drain grease; add soup, water, rice and salt and pepper.
Boil bell peppers in about 3-inches of water until tender (around 15 minutes).
Stuff peppers with meat mixture and wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange pineapple milkshake
directions: In blender, combine orange juice, pineapple and ice cream. Blend until smooth and frothy.

title: apricot-nut squares
directions: Cream sugar and eggs first; mix remaining ingredients in order, except jars of filling.
Take 1/3 or little more.
Spread in greased cookie sheet pan to fill bottom.
Take 1 jar put on half of dough, take other jar and put over second half of dough.
Take remaining cookie dough and sprinkle on top over nut-apricot.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: evelyn's ice box fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size bowl until all ingredients stick together. Put on a piece of wax paper and roll into a log or ball.
Put on a cookie sheet and put in freezer for 24 hours. Take out of freezer, cut into slices and enjoy.

title: banana frosting
directions: Beat until it forms peaks.
Use electric beater.
Very good also on date nut cake.

title: cold pea salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas and onions in large salad bowl.
Combine remaining vegetables; place on top of lettuce.
Mix salt, pepper, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spread over salad; seal edges.
Chill overnight.
Crumble bacon on top.
Serves 16.
(This recipe is easily halved to serve eight people).

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onions,
celery
and
carrots
in
oleo.
In large pot put beef
and
vegetables with tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Add oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1 hour or more.

title: egg casserole
directions: Place buttered bread in bottom of 5 x 13-inch baking dish (pregreased).
Pour egg and milk mixture over bread.
Crumble bacon and cheese over this.
Let refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix egg, lemon juice, sugar, salt and mustard 70 seconds in blender, adding oil in a steady stream through opening in top while motor is running.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Pour the boiling vinegar over the cucumbers in jars and seal. Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: johnny mozetti
directions: Fry meat until brown and then add vegetables; fry well.
Mix sauce and bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms and stuffed olives to sauce mixture.
Cook noodles and drain.
Place noodles in bottom of large roasting pan.
Add cooked meat, vegetables and sauce; mix all thoroughly.
Grate cheese over top.
Put cover on roasting pan and bake slowly 1 hour.

title: orange date nut cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Bake at 250° for 1 3/4 hours in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix together and drop by the spoonfuls in greased hot skillet. Brown on both sides and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: coconut supreme
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, softened margarine and chopped nuts together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: magic cookies
directions: Place ingredients in shallow pan (9 x 13-inch) in layers as listed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Pour into container.
Freeze overnight.
Take a couple of scoops out and put in glass.
Pour 7-Up over mixture.

title: taffy
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar and vinegar in saucepan.
Cook to hard ball stage or 260° on candy thermometer, stirring frequently. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and butter.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Spread on buttered dish.
Let stand until cool enough to handle. Pull taffy with buttered hands until firm.
Yields 24 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Add milk and egg to dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in molasses and fat.
Pour batter into greased pan (square).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili-mushroom caps
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until almost crisp.
Remove from skillet; chop.
Drain fat from skillet.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop 2/3 of stems.
Save stems from remaining mushrooms for soup making or other uses.
Cook mushroom caps in boiling water 1 minute.
Drain; rinse under cold water.
Drain on paper towel.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix with rest of ingredients. Let rise until about doubled.
Punch dough down.
In muffin pan, place dough in each cup or 3 small balls in each for cloverleaf rolls.
This can also be baked in a loaf pan for bread.
Bake at 325° until tops are golden.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp in cold water.
Combine all ingredients and mix well until creamy.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Best if made a day before.
Serve with Ritz or Sociable crackers.

title: hot bean dip
directions: In a large saucepan, place all ingredients; mix well.
Add tomato and a small amount of bacon grease.
Pour all into a baking pan and bake at 450° for 1 hour.
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: country fried steak with gravy
directions: Dip cubed steak in flour that has been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown both sides of meat in 1/4 cup vegetable oil.

title: green beans casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except onion rings) in saucepan.
Mix good.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Then pour into casserole dish.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cut in small pieces.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate and allow to mellow and cool for several hours.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake.
Empty into roasting pan and bake 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bake until brown.

title: lemon c pie
directions: Mix milk, butter, lemon juice and rind.
Add eggs, one at a time, mix well.
Mix sugar, cornmeal, flour and salt.
Blend into first mixture.
Place in 9 or 10-inch pie crust.
Cook 45 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix well and put in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Roll in crushed nuts, paprika, chives or parsley.

title: magical mint kiss
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy. Mix flour and cocoa and gradually add to butter mixture. Beat well. Mold 1 tablespoon around each chocolate Kiss. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool 1 minute. Remove and cool and roll in the powdered sugar x 2.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Drain eggplant and mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add alternately with milk to egg mixture.
Add extracts and poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 lightly greased and floured loaf pans.

title: sugar-free splenda pudding pie
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch and Splenda.
Add egg yolks and milk. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in milk; cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat, cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove from the heat, gradually stir about 1 cup of hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Return all to saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until nearly boiling.
Reduce heat; cook and stir about 2 minutes more (do not boil).
Remove from heat; stir in one cup coconut, butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix soup, pimento, carrots, onions, salt, pepper, margarine and sour cream.
Fold in squash.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Mix vegetables.
In a large bowl, layer half the cornbread (crumbled), half of the vegetables and half of the dressing.
Repeat layers with other half and then top with crumbled, crisp bacon.

title: raisin-apple bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder in a bowl; stir.
Add raisins, egg and applesauce; stir until batter is well moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Grease four 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Fill about 2/3 full with batter.
Place in preheated 350° oven; bake 45 minutes or until loaves test done. Cool 10 minutes.
Turn bread out of pans to cool completely. Makes 4 small loaves.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer hamburger, then layer potatoes and onions.
Cover those first layers with 1/2 of Cheez Whiz.
Layer again as before. Add the rest of the Cheez Whiz. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mr. nick's chili
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot.
Sprinkle with flour.
(The thickness depends on amount of flour.)
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Stir and break up any big pieces of meat with spoon. Let simmer for 1 hour, the longer the better.
If it gets too thick, add water and continue to cook a little longer.
Ready to eat or let cool and freeze.
May add canned chili beans or canned crowder peas, if desired.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor.
Put into medium size covered bowl.
Grind up orange and apple.
Add pecans and marshmallows.
Grind them also.
Add to cranberries.
Stir in sugar to taste and strawberry Jell-O.
Best if left in refrigerator overnight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese set out until room temperature, then work sausage, cheese and Bisquick together until well blended. Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: red beans & rice
directions: Cook sausage in oven & set aside. Cook beans, onion, garlic, and seasonings 20 minutes. Add sliced sausage plus 1 Tbsp. sausage fat to bean mixture. Simmer for about 45 minutes. Serve over rice. Serves 7 to 8. I like cornbread with this.

title: western
directions: Beat eggs and add onion, green pepper and ham.
Heat butter in skillet. Scramble mixture in butter until done.
Serve on toast with lettuce, tomato and mayonnaise.

title: oatmeal pumpkin bread or cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in loaf pan or cupcake pan at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown
beef
and
onions.
Add
cumin,
garlic,
chili powder, salt, pepper and water and simmer.	Put 1/3 taco sauce on bottom of casserole,
then 1/2 of tortillas and then 1/3 of taco sauce.
Add beef
mix, then sour cream and 1/2 of cheese. Place rest of
tortillas,
then taco sauce and rest of cheese. Cover with foil.	Bake
minutes
Remove foil for the last few minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Slice bananas.
Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks. In large bowl, mix bananas, mandarin oranges, pineapple and fruit cocktail with its juice.
Spoon fruit into dessert bowls; sprinkle with coconut.

title: jello shots
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup water.
Add 1 cup of vodka.
Mix together.
Pour into small shot size plastic cups available at warehouse or restaurant supply stores.
Set cups on tray; refrigerate until set.
"Drink" outta cups after Jell-O is set.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Start heating oven to moderate 350°.
Place ingredients in layers in a 2-quart baking dish with tight-fitting lid.
Layer rice, then corn.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water over first layers.
Layer onion and pepper, then ground beef.
Pour second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can water over all.
Cover meat with the bacon.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and mix with all other ingredients.
Then roll into a ball.

title: broiled shrimp bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients. Spread on bread slices. Broil until browned and bubbles.

title: cranberry-nut coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix brown sugar, walnuts and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine baking mix, granulated sugar, egg and milk or water; beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Spread batter in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar mix and spoon cranberry sauce over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
While warm, spread with Confectioners Sugar Icing.

title: no-bake fruit cocktail cake
directions: Place in a 3-quart saucepan milk, marshmallows and orange juice.
Heat until marshmallows melt.
Take pan off heat and stir in dates, pecans, fruit cocktail and cherries.

title: fried beef liver with onions
directions: Cut liver in serving-size pieces; coat with flour.
Heat oil in frying pan and cook liver over medium heat until brown on both sides; drain on paper towels.
Cook the onions in same skillet until tender.
Salt and pepper onions and liver.
Drain excess fat from onions.
Put onions on liver to serve.

title: oven fries
directions: Wash and then cut each potato lengthwise into 8 spears.
Pat dry with paper towels (remove surface moisture).
Place potatoes in a large jelly roll pan.
Drizzle with oil and mix well with your hands.
Arrange pieces, cut sides up, in a single layer. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden in color.

title: minted trout - american indian(taos indian is minted trout)
directions: Mix either garden or fresh wild mint (yerba buena) with 1 tablespoon salt and 1/2 cup olive or cooking oil.
Mash the mint with a spoon to release the flavor to the oil.
Then fill the cavity of a trout with the oily mint leaves.
Also wrap the trout with mint leaves and bind with one or two strips of bacon (according to the size of the trout).
Secure the bacon with a round toothpick.
Broil over charcoal, or under a broiler until the bacon is cooked.
The bacon will baste the trout with its oils and flavor and the mint will release its herbal taste to the trout, too.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together.
Fold in cherry pie filling, drained pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
I make this fruit salad at Christmas.

title: corn pie
directions: In a small bowl, mix the first 5 ingredients.
Pour melted butter over crushed Ritz crackers.
Stir until all cracker crumbs are moist with the melted butter.
Press crumbs around in pan and form crust.
Pour corn mixture into the crust.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted into center comes out clean, and top of pie is brown.
If desired, save 1/4 cup of cracker crumbs for top and dot with butter.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and divide into 3 parts.
Roll out on floured board and wrap in Saran Wrap overnight.
Bake at 325° for 18 minutes or until done.

title: ginger ale aspic salad
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water and dissolve in ginger ale.
Stir in the lemon juice and the 1 1/2 cups of ginger ale and chill to set until syrupy.
Add rest of the ingredients and chill until firm.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: world's tastiest brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter two 8-inch square baking pans or 1 (9 x 13 x 2-inch) pan.

title: banana nut snacks
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Line 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan with foil. Coat foil with nonstick cooking spray.

title: pineapple sauce for ham
directions: Put brown sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in crushed pineapple with juice, lemon juice and mustard.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it thickens and boils.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: buttered crunch
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over low heat.
Stir in salt. Add cereal.
Stir until all pieces are coated.
Continue to heat and stir for 5 minutes or until cereal is lightly toasted. Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese and stir to coat.
Spread on absorbent paper towel to cool.

title: meat loaf cups
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; add egg.
Stir well.
Add onion, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning. Mix thoroughly.
Add meat.
Mix well and fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Brush with catsup and corn syrup mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add everything else.
Add grated cheddar cheese and sour cream to each individual bowl. Crunch handful of Tostitos on top.
Stir and enjoy!

title: egg casserole
directions: Cook meat and crumble in bottom of large rectangular pan. Cube bread and put on top of meat.
Mix thoroughly, eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread.
Cover with cheese.
Chill 12 to 24 hours.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Add milk and cream; cook until thick. Add cheese,
crabmeat,
mushrooms,
salt and pepper to taste. Pour in casserole dish;
sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix all together and cook a few minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer on the bottom of Doritos or nacho chips.
Next, put meat mixture in and then another layer of chips.
Top with Cheddar cheese (use as much as you like).
Bake 20 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine oleo and cracker crumbs.
Pat into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs on high speed of an electric mixer until light (4 minutes).
Add powdered sugar, softened oleo and vanilla. Beat 5 minutes.
Spread over crumbs; chill 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning and water and cook 15 minutes.
Place lettuce on serving plates; top with onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Crumble chips on top.
Pour hamburger and juice over top. Pour avocado mixture over meat and top with taco sauce.
Garnish with halved black olives.
Serves 6.

title: cornmeal pancakes
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking soda, salt and sugar in a bowl. Make a well and add buttermilk, 2 teaspoons of oil and egg yolk. Mix well; carefully fold in egg white.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Fry on hot griddle or pan using oil as needed.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, melted butter, vanilla, white vinegar, pecans and coconut.
Pour into unbaked 8 1/2 or 9-inch deep dish pie shell and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn bread fritters
directions: Mix ingredients well!
Drop by tablespoon into deep fryer. Cook 5 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients and sift over blueberries.
Add remaining flour mixture over batter alternately with milk.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Brown meat separately.
Combine them and add Ro-Tel in 2-quart casserole bowl.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: helen's watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, place in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Smooth top with spoon and refrigerate till ready to use.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in 1 cup milk.
Add onion, meat, egg and seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls and saute in butter in skillet until lightly browned on all sides.
Remove from pan.
Blend flour into butter remaining in skillet.
Add water, bouillon cube, 1/2 cup milk and the cream.
Cook and stir until smooth and slightly thickened.
Add the meatballs; cover and simmer gently 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut franks into 1-inch pieces.
Pull small piece of dough, enough to wrap around frank.
Fold ends of dough over frank, pinch seam to seal.

title: slush fruit cup
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients, except ginger ale; mix well, then add ginger ale.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover; freeze about 4 hours or until slushy.
Serve in individual dishes; garnish with fresh fruit, if desired.

title: beat-n-eat frosting
directions: Mix egg white, sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla in small deep bowl.
Add boiling water and beat until stiff peaks form.

title: greek style spinach salad
directions: In small bowl, combine yogurt, lemon juice, dill, sugar and pepper, mixing well.
In large bowl, combine spinach, Feta cheese, tomatoes, cucumber and green onion.
Pour dressing over salad and toss until combined.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together. Hull out French bread. Stuff mixture into French bread and cook at 350° until mixture bubbles.
Serve with corn chips.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions for a 9 x 13-inch pan. Punch holes in surface of hot cake.
Mix milk and coconut cream; pour over hot cake.
Allow to cool.

title: chicken layer casserole
directions: Place ingredients in bottom of baking pan.

title: butter sauce
directions: Mix the sugar, cornstarch and salt well.
Stir in the hot water and cook, stirring, until clear and thick.
Add butter and vanilla; cool.
This is delicious with any cake or pudding.

title: old "toddle house" waffles(good)
directions: Beat well in mixer.
Mix all as listed and put in waffle iron 1/2 cupful at a time.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Crumble crackers with rolling pin.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Place broccoli in a buttered casserole dish.
Cut cheese into slices and place on top of broccoli.
Melt margarine; add to crackers and mix well.
Spread over broccoli and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jello and pineapple
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple; leave slices in can.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Pour into can.
Chill at least 3 hours. To unmold, dip can in hot water and cut out bottom, placing a saucer or your hand under the open end of can while removing other end.
Push mold out.
Cut between pineapple slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: western dip
directions: Blend together and serve.

title: potato casserole supreme
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and beat in large bowl of electric mixer until fluffy, adding butter, seasonings and milk.
Check seasonings, turn into buttered shallow casserole. Fold cheese into whipped cream and spread over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Casserole may be prepared ahead of time, the topping added just before baking.
Yields 10 servings.

title: pineapple twist
directions: Too many husbands are spoiled by improper cooking.
Some are kept in hot water too long.
Others are frozen, some are always in a stew and some constantly in a pickle.
Naturally, they'll never become good and tender managed this way.
In selecting, don't be guided by the silvery appearance, as you would in a mackerel or golden tint as a salmon.
Be sure to select him yourself, but don't go to the market.
Those brought to the door are best.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a little oil.
Add salt and pepper.
When brown, drain off oil.
Mix soup, catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over pork chops.
Simmer for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: apple peanut cream spread
directions: Press grated apple with paper towel to absorb excess moisture. Toss grated apple with lemon juice.
In small bowl combine cream cheese, peanut butter, honey and cinnamon.
Beat until fluffy and light.
Stir in apple.
Yields 1 cup.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken. Remove from broth. Cool. Melt butter in baking dish (13 x 9). Add chicken to butter. Add 2 cans Veg-All, drained. Mix soups, flour, milk and broth together. Pour over top. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine
sugar, cocoa, salt, flour, cornmeal and pecans in
a medium
bowl; mix well.
Combine eggs, milk, butter and vanilla; stir
into	dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake
at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until pie is set.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown.
Drain, spread into pie plate.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper and Bisquick until smooth.
Fifteen second in blender on high or 1 minutes with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate, bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese, bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (5 to 8 minutes).
Cool before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add eggs.
Add butter and vanilla; blend in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into frozen pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Shape into 20 small meatballs. Brown well in oil.
Drain excess fat.
Sprinkle flour over meatballs, stir gently to coat meatballs.
Combine tomatoes, Heinz 57 sauce, sugar and salt; pour over meatballs. simmer uncovered 25 minutes or until sauce is of desired consistency, stirring occasionally.
Server meatballs and sauce over noodles.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pasta with kraut and sausage
directions: Brown sausage using seasoning until done.
Boil pasta until done.
Drain.
Combine pasta, sausage, kraut and mushrooms in crock-pot.
Let simmer on low about 1 hour.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs, margarine and sugar together.
Press firmly into 9 x 13-inch glass or metal dish.
Make up Dream Whip according to package and whip cream cheese into Dream Whip mixture.
Add powdered sugar.
Put cherry pie filling on top of crumbs and spread cream cheese mixture on top of that.
You can use any kind of pie or fresh fruit filling you choose.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: pie crust
directions: In a bowl, put flour
and add salt (stir). Add Crisco, mash it around until it makes a crumbly consistency.
Then add water.
Do not overwork the dough.

title: special dressing
directions: Blend and store in jar.

title: mouth-watering apricot bars
directions: Press 2/3 of the mixture into a 9 x 9-inch ungreased pan. Spread apricot filling evenly over the oatmeal mixture and top with the remaining oatmeal mixture.
Press lightly.
Bake 35 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.
Cut into squares.
Makes 20 to 24 bars.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Sift flour and baking powder, set aside.
Beat eggs thoroughly. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add 3 c of flour to mixture. Sprinkle remaining flour onto a large platter and knead dough. Don't roll too thin.
Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown. Store after cooled, in air tight container.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over melted butter; do not stir. Combine peaches and remaining sugar.
Add 1 tablespoon cinnamon, 1 teaspoon cloves and a touch of nutmeg.
Heat in a pan until it comes to a boil.
Pour over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook mushrooms in margarine.
Add chicken and heat.
Add soup and sour cream.
Blend and turn off.
In a 10 x 15-inch pan (9 x 13-inch is not large enough), place 1/2 of cooked spaghetti.
Stir in 1/2 of soup mixture.
Add rest of spaghetti and soup mixture; stir in.
Cover top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, approximately 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves lots!

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Chop pretzels in food processor until fine. Blend with sugar and butter. Press into 9 x 13 pan and bake 10 minutes in 350° oven. Cool.

title: confetti spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti. In large skillet cook beef, green pepper and onion until beef is cooked. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, brown sugar, salt, chili powder, pepper and garlic powder. Drain spaghetti, add to the beef mixture. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 in. baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle cheese over top. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cram together the oleo, sugar and Crisco. Add the 5 egg yolks (one at a time), vanilla and buttermilk alternately with 2 cups all-purpose flour, soda, salt, pecans and coconut. Beat egg whites; fold into batter.
Bake at 350° in 3 layer pans.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Soften butter; add to yeast mixture along with sugar, salt, oleo, eggs, potatoes and 4 cups flour. Beat until smooth with mixer.
Add remaining flour.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead.
Place in greased bowl; refrigerate overnight.
Dough can be kept up to 5 days.
Shape rolls; let rise 1 1/2 hours, then bake.

title: potato chip sandwich
directions: Put Miracle Whip on one side of each slice of bread.
Put potato chips on one piece of bread.
Put lettuce leaf on other piece of bread.
Smash bread slices together.
Put it on a plate and then it's ready.

title: "grandma's chili"
directions: Note:
Can add more meat, pepper, onion and seasonings according to your taste.

title: sugarless pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together sweetening, shortening and eggs.
Beat well. Add pineapple and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spectacular pie
directions: Add water to pineapple syrup to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling. Dissolve Jell-O in syrup.
Blend 1/2 cup of the gelatin with the cream cheese.
When smooth, pour into pie shell; chill until set. Arrange pineapple chunks on the set pie filling.
Spoon remaining 1/2 cup of Jell-O over all and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot mold
directions: Heat nectar; dissolve jello.
Add junior apricots, frozen orange juice and lemon juice.
Add seltzer.
Pour into mold.
May be served with mayonnaise-lemon juice sauce.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with damp paper towels.
In large bowl, combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, garlic salt and pepper.
Add chicken, coating each piece well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, preheat the oven to 350°. Remove chicken from sour cream mixture; roll in bread crumbs, coating gently.
Arrange in single layer in shallow pan.
Heat butter and shortening in small saucepan; spoon 1/2 over chicken. Bake chicken, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Spoon remainder of butter and shortening over chicken and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until tender.

title: katie's salad dressing
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients, then mix all ingredients except milk and Miracle Whip and let come to a boil.
Add the milk and Miracle Whip.
Blend and let come to a boil.
Use over potatoes, cabbage, tossed salad or macaroni.
Store any leftovers in refrigerator.

title: slumgullion
directions: Put water on to cook macaroni.
Saute onion in butter, margarine or cooking oil.
When the onion is translucent, add hamburger and cook until brown, breaking it up.
Cook macaroni. Add tomato paste, water, oregano, garlic salt and ground pepper to hamburger.
Boil gently until most of the water has evaporated. When macaroni is done, drain and add to hamburger mixture. Ketchup can be added on top to sweeten.
Serve with bread and a green salad.

title: cookie crunch bars
directions: You will need sucker sticks.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until soft.
Blend to puree or use potato masher.
Return to saucepan and add cheese, Velveeta and cream cheese.
Heat over low until cheese melts.
Add milk to desired consistency.
Add few steamed broccoli flowers when serving.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add chips, chopped candy bar and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These are also good with vanilla chips and pecans.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook beef until it begins to get tender and add rest of ingredients.
Cook until tender, adding water as necessary. Cooking time about 2 hours.
This is a low fat, low calorie dish.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add the remainder of ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased casserole dish.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place cornmeal with flour in a mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk and beat well.
Add egg whites and oil; mix well.
Coat muffin tins with a nonstick spray and fill 2/3 full. Bake for 15 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to boil and boil 5 minutes. Let cool.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Serve with ice.

title: upper crust chicken
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Combine bread crusts, chicken, celery, onion and 1 3/4 cups cheese.
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange bread slices over chicken mix. Combine mayonnaise, eggs, seasoning and gradually add milk until well blended.
Pour over bread and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 325° or until it browns.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Cook noodles until tender.
Place layer of noodles in 9 x 13 pan.
Put 1/2 the onion and 1/2 the celery and 1/2 the chicken along with 1 can of soup on top of noodles.
Then add remaining noodles, followed by remaining onion, celery, chicken and other can of soup.
Pour chicken broth over top.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy, delicious raspberry cream dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in raspberries, then ice cream
until
well blended. Refrigerate until set.	Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning; let simmer. Melt cheese and add tomatoes until thick.
Crush a bag of Doritos and add to tossed salad and olives.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Serve while cheese is hot.
May top with sour cream.
Serves 4 for a meal or 8 for snacks.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli.
Saute onion and celery in butter. Melt Cheez Whiz.
Put rice, broccoli, onion and Cheez Whiz in an ungreased casserole dish and mix.
Blend in soup and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: milk chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or center is set.
Cool 10 minutes in pans on wire racks. Remove from pans and cool completely.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and granulated sugar at medium speed with mixer until creamy.

title: sweet potatoes and apple casserole
directions: Boil potatoes 20 to 25 minutes until tender.
Peel.
Peel and core apple, slice in 1/4-inch rings.
Melt 1 teaspoon butter and brown apple slices.
Butter shallow casserole dish large enough to hold potatoes flat after slicing them 1/2 to 3/4-inches thick. Sprinkle with salt and top with apple slices.
Squeeze lemon juice over all.
Pour maple syrup over all.
Dot with remaining butter. Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes until sweet potatoes absorb syrup.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely! Combine remaining ingredients, except frosting.
Beat 10 to 15 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Spread over cooled cake.
Open can of frosting and soften over low heat in pan of water or in microwave.
Top with softened frosting.

title: jumbo cheese shells
directions: Cook shells according to package.
Combine all ingredients, except spaghetti sauce.
Fill each shell.
Spread thin layer of spaghetti sauce in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place shells in single layer; cover with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Spray Pam on a small fry pan, non-stick.
Cook on both sides.
Put on plate, spread 1 tsp diet butter, sprinkle with cinnamon and another pack sweetener or brown sugar substitute.
Roll up like burrito.
Delicious when stuffed with favorite fruit (cooked or fresh).

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and heat iron skillet.
Brown meat and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except meat and cheese. Place 1/2 of cornbread mixture in skillet and top with 1/2 meat and 1/2 cheese.
Add other 1/2 of cornbread mixture and top with other 1/2 of meat and other 1/2 of cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: salmon patty spread
directions: Mix salmon and cream cheese; blend well.
Add lemon juice, onion and horseradish.
Mix until well blended.
Can be shaped into log, ball, etc.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Chill, serve with crackers.

title: cheese cake
directions: Before mixing have all ingredients at room temperature for 2 hours.
Then beat cream cheese, one block at a time.
Add sugar and beat again; then add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.

title: sugar free pecan pie
directions: Blend eggs in bowl with fructose, vanilla and salt. Mix thoroughly. Stir in maple syrup, mix well. Add nuts; stir until all are coated well. Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: shrimp tomato cloud
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on top of cold water to dissolve.
Bring soup to boil in 3-quart saucepan over a heat controlled top burner set at 212°.
Or over a medium flame, then remove from burner.
Add cream cheese and stir until smooth, then add mayonnaise, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in water-gelatin mixture, lemon juice and pepper. Fold in shrimp, celery, onion, Tabasco and horseradish.
Add celery salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.
Pour into thoroughly oiled 2 1/2-quart mold and refrigerate until very firm (several hours), or overnight, if possible.
Serve with mild crackers. Serves party of 30 or more.
Cut recipe in half for small party.

title: hawaiian chop suey
directions: Cook hamburg until light brown.
Add rest of the ingredients. Cook until done.
Serve over Chinese noodles or rice.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into large ball.
Flatten a bit and, with a floured knife, cut a cross into the dough.
Place in buttered, floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: volteado de pina(pineapple upside-down cake)
directions: Coat bottom and sides of 9 1/2-inch spring-form pan with 3 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine. Arrange pineapple on sugar.
Cut extra slices in half and stand on sides of pan.
Place a cherry in center of each pineapple slice. Fill in spaces between slice with pecan halves.
Combine remaining butter and sugar.
Cream until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Spoon batter evenly over pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Remove side of pan.
Invert on serving plate.
Remove pan bottom.
Makes 1 (9 1/2-inch) cake.

title: cheese dogs
directions: Lay tortillas on cookie sheet.
Lay a slice of cheese on each tortilla.
Put frank on top of that and roll.
Put a toothpick in the cheese dogs so they won't come unrolled.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: blt
directions: Toast two pieces of bread and put the other ingredients inside.

title: coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Frost when cool.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 15 minutes.

title: jean's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa, then egg yolks and milk. Thicken on top of stove in saucepan.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Beat the egg whites.
Add dash of cream of tartar and 1/4 teaspoon sugar.
Cover with meringue and bake in oven until meringue is golden brown.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour one can cherry pie filling over mixture. Spread remaining batter over pie filling.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook onion and potatoes; drain and save juice.
Add soup, milk, butter, grease and bacon to potatoes.
Simmer a few minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.
If too thick, add some of potato juice.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown chicken in oil.
When brown, remove from pot.
Add onions, pepper, parsley and green onions; saute until onions are clear.
Add sausage, rice, stock, garlic, chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook until nearly all water has boiled out, then reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Let simmer until rice is done, about 1 hour.
Do not lift lid for 1 hour.

title: tasty party hors d'oeuvres
directions: Over medium heat, melt 1 tablespoon butter; cook onion, until tender.
Remove from heat.	Squeeze spinach dry; stir in with Fontina, tuna, cream
cheese,
pepper and egg.
Cut stack of phyllo lengthwise into
strips.	Place
strips
on waxed paper; cover with damp paper towels.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: mushroom & swiss cheese quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter for 3 minutes.
In another pan, saute bacon until crisp and drain on absorbent paper.
Combine mushrooms and bacon; add cheese and onion.
Turn mixture into pie shell.
Stir cream, nutmeg and pepper into eggs.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 300 and bake 30 minutes longer. Garnish with red pepper and black olives.
Makes 8 large servings.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, oil, salt, pepper and water for 30 seconds. Cool and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: squash with sour cream
directions: Cook squash; drain well and mash.
Add butter, bouillon cube, onion,
then beaten egg and sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese and crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Spread bread cubes in bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Spread sauerkraut over bread cubes; then layer corned beef strips over sauerkraut. Pour dressing over all. Spray aluminum foil with cooking spray & cover dish. Bake 20 minutes. Remove cover, sprinkle with cheese and bake uncovered 10 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add vegetable soup to hamburger and simmer for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile prepare mashed potatoes according to directions.
Pour hamburger into casserole dish. "Ice" hamburger with potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in saucepan.
Beat egg yolk; add to milk and pour into pan with sugar and cornstarch. Cook over low heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly. Remove from stove; add vanilla, butter and food coloring.
Put one cup of coconut into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Make meringue from egg white that you have set aside.
Pour filling into pie shell; cover with meringue.
Spread the other cup of coconut over meringue.
Place in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain sweet potatoes and arrange in casserole dish.
Make 5 cuts partially through loaf of Spam.
Drain fruit, saving juice. Combine cornstarch and brown sugar.
Stir in juice and margarine. Heat to boil.
Stir in fruit and simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon over loaf and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and other seasonings.
Mix together.
Coat chicken.
Place coated chicken on greased baking pan.
Bake for 35 minutes or until done.

title: helen mary's chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper. Brown in a 375° oven in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
To chicken, add the onion, potatoes, mushrooms and artichokes. Combine remaining ingredients to form a sauce.
Pour sauce over chicken, etc.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Delicious served over very thin pasta.

title: larry's chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic cloves in butter or oleo.
Brown meat. Combine onion and garlic with meat in a large pot.
Pour in beans (you can use precooked dry pintos) and tomato juice.
Add enough water to fill pot.
Bring to a boil; then simmer 2 to 3 hours. Salt and pepper to taste.
If you do not like a lot of tomato taste you can substitute 1 can of beef broth and 2 (8 ounce) cans of tomato sauce.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs. Add crumbs and milk alternately to mixture. Add nuts, coconut and vanilla. Put in well-greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy double decker fudge
directions: In double boiler, combine peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Cook, stirring after 1 minute, until chips are melted and the mixture is smooth.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and spread evenly into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar; spread on 1st layer that has cooled. Combine pudding mixes and milk; beat until thick. Spread over cream cheese layer. Mix Cool Whip and vanilla. Spread on pudding layer just before serving.

title: francine's pasta fagioli
directions: Brown garlic in olive oil.
Chop celery (with leaves) into 2 or 3-inch pieces and add to garlic.
Add tomato paste, beans and water.
Season with salt & pepper.
Let sauce simmer.
Cook pasta and drain water, leaving enough water to cover pasta 1-2 inches over.
When sauce is done, add to pasta and water.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add marshmallows.
Stir to partially dissolve.
Add sugar, oranges, salt and cottage cheese. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Add whipped cream; pour into mold.

title: noodles
directions: Put all together and mix.
Add enough flour (1 cup) until sticky.
Roll thin as for pie crust.
Dry for about 1 hour, cut. Can use immediately or freeze.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight jar.
Use approximately 2 teaspoons in cup.
Pour hot water over mix.

title: summer pasta sauce
directions: Brown garlic in olive oil.
Add parsley and anchovy paste. Pour in 1 can stewed tomatoes, dash of salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over pasta!
Serves 4.

title: miracle cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish, allowing it to cover bottom; grease side of dish.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over melted margarine.
Over batter, pour quart of fruit.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: bran muffins
directions: In saucepan mix together milk, orange juice and raisins. Heat 2 or 3 minutes.
Cover to plump.
Stir together flour, sugar, orange peel, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Add orange juice mixture to bran cereal and oats, stir.
Let stand until cereal is softened.
To cereal mixture add oil and eggs, beat well.
Add flour mixture then stir just till combined.
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full with batter.
Bake 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields: 12 muffins.

title: shortnin' bread
directions: Mix the flour and brown sugar together thoroughly.
Add the butter and work in until a smooth dough is formed.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface and pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
(Dough is easier to handle when chilled.)
Cut dough into desired shapes and transfer to cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until very delicately browned.
Remove sheets to cooling racks for 5 minutes before transferring cookies to racks to cool thoroughly. Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine in order of listing.
Batter is very thick.
Bake at 325°
in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: applesauce ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 10-inch loaf pan with aluminum foil.
Place pineapple in bottom.
Combine all ingredients, except sugar, butter and cloves.
Pack into pan with back of spoon; unmold into shallow baking pan.
Combine sugar and butter; spread on ham mixture.
Dot with cloves.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, lemon juice and eggs in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Let cool completely.
Add Cool Whip, grapes, coconut, pineapple (drained), oranges, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well. Keep refrigerated.

title: sherried tuna in toast cups
directions: Drain mushrooms. Add enough milk to liquid to make 1 1/2 cups. Cook mushrooms and green pepper in butter over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Blend in flour and salt. Gradually add reserved liquid and cook, stirring constantly, until thickens and boils. Add cream to egg yolks.
Stir into sauce.
Add tuna and pimento.
Heat.
Stir in sherry.

title: katie's barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in a single layer in baking pan. Add enough water to generously cover the bottom of the pan. Cover with foil and bake in low oven (250°) for about 4 hours. Check occasionally and add water if necessary. Drain water and let ribs sit at room temperature until completely cooled. Break cooled ribs into large bite-size pieces, removing any fat or bones. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan. Gently boil for about 15 minutes or until desired thickness. Mix sauce with meat and gently heat. Can be served alone or on buns.

title: good-n-easy salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple (undrained) with the pudding, pouring the dry pudding into the pineapple. Stir and add marshmallows, whipped topping, nuts and coconut.
Stir by hand.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken casserole(king ranch chicken)
directions: Whisk together soups, milk, chiles and salsa (you may use 1/2 cup of either salsa or chiles instead of 1/4 cup of each).
Stir in the cooked, cut up chicken.
Spray baking dish with nonstick coating or grease it, then layer 3 or 4 torn tortillas, soup and chicken mixture and grated cheese.
Continue layering until dish is full.
(For a 3-quart Corning dish it should take about 3 ladles of soup and chicken mixture per layer.)
This recipe makes about two casseroles in 3-quart dishes.
One can be frozen for later use.

title: russian meatballs
directions: Add your own favorite meat spices, i.e., onion, steak, garlic spice.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Pour over carrots and let stand overnight.
Keeps two weeks refrigerated.

title: frosting cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, water and cake mix together.
Add frosting. Mix well.
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot.

title: lemon or chocolate lush
directions: Cut oleo into other ingredients as for pastry until crumbly. Spread and pat gently in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes; cool.

title: easy but elegant meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, egg, onion and salt. Shape into small balls. Combine in a large frying pan the chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice. Heat to simmering.
Drop meatballs into sauce and simmer until brown.

title: irish coffee(microwave)
directions: Dissolve sugar in black coffee glass or a heat-resistant, non-metallic glass, cup or mug.
(Do not use a glass with metallic trim.)
Heat uncovered on Full power 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until hot (160°).
Stir in Irish whiskey.
Carefully float a spoonful of whipped cream on top.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients and cook on rangetop for 15 to 20 minutes over low-medium setting.
Spread liberally on chicken wings and cook in the oven for 45 minutes at 350°.
(Any sauce left over may be used to baste the wings midway through the cooking time.)

title: dog biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first seven ingredients.
Mix in bacon drippings and egg.
Add enough water to form a ball.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 25 to 30 minutes.
Bone appetite.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine ham, rice, onion, garlic, Tony Chachere seasoning, cinnamon and eggs.
Form into rolls.
Remove core from large head of cabbage and separate individual leaves.
Blanch each leaf for 1 minute in boiling water and immediately fill with stuffing; roll and secure with toothpick.
Into Dutch oven, place tomatoes, onion and bell peppers.
Place cabbage rolls in Dutch oven with sauce mixture; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: spinach chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken breasts into pieces.
Cook.
Stir with onion 6-8 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove from heat.
Add spinach.
Mix well.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, and seasonings, mix well.
Stir 3/4 cup of the soup mixture into chicken and spinach.
Divide evenly into tortillas.
Roll up and place seam down in 13 x 9-inch inch pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Pour remaining soup mixture over enchiladas.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven 5-10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chili powder (optional).

title: 5 minute fudge for the girls
directions: Place Carnation milk and sugar in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling, then cook 5 minutes.
Begin timing after mixture begins bubbling around edges of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir fudge until marshmallows and chocolate are melted.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend first four ingredients with electric mixer until smooth. Serve with sliced apples.

title: cherry-cheese coffee cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and extract until smooth. Remove rolls from cans and arrange the 16 pieces, overlapping each other, around a pizza pan with long points in the center and the other long end hanging over edge of pan.

title: deep fried shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp; pat dry.
Mix remaining ingredients. Heat fryer to 375°.
Dip shrimp in batter; fry until golden brown.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Sprinkle top with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: cookies and cream pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Combine Oreos and Cool Whip in a separate bowl.
Stir pudding into Cool Whip and Oreo mixture. Pour into pie shell and freeze for 3 to 4 hours.
Let stand about 20 minutes before serving.

title: rich rice pudding
directions: Mix milk, rice and peels in a large saucepan; bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes, stirring often or until mixture thickens and starts to stick to bottom of pan.
Reduce heat to very low; cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly until mixture is very thick.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly; add vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Before serving, stir in heavy cream, then spoon into dessert glasses.
Top with garnishes. Yields six 1/2-cup servings.

title: ambrosia cream squares
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter and next 3 ingredients.
Put them in well-greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Chill.

title: big al's marinade
directions: Add all of the ingredients to a pot and bring to a boil.
Stir until combined.
Cool to room temperature and bottle.
Store in refrigerator.
Use as a marinade for beef, chicken and pork.
Best when marinated overnight.

title: orange chantilly cream
directions: Cut a thin slice off the top of each orange. With a grapefruit knife, cut around inside of orange. Scoop out the orange pulp. Invert oranges onto paper towels to drain. Remove and discard membranes from orange pulp; set pulp aside.

title: homemade pasta
directions: Place flour in bowl.
Make well in center.
Place eggs in well and beat with fork.
Gradually draw the flour into the eggs.
Mix constantly.
If moist, add more flour.
It may not use all the flour.
Let rest a few minutes.
Knead on floured surface for 8 minutes.
Cover dough with plastic (or bowl).
Let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Knead dough for 1 minute.
Roll dough to desired thickness and cut to desired type.
Cook pasta in boiling water until tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage cheese crumbles
directions: Combine all ingredients well by hand.
Form into small balls size of walnuts. Can bake immediately or refrigerate, then bake, or freeze and bake later.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine cake mix, eggs, water, flour and oil in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 32 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely.

title: "tiropetes" - cheese triangles
directions: Combine the cheeses and stir; add eggs, one at a time and mix well.
Cut each pastry sheet into 3-inch strips and brush with melted butter.
Place 1 teaspoon of the filling on each strip and fold over to make a triangle.
Continue folding from side to side in the form of a triangle.
Proceed this way for the length of strip for each triangle.

title: all american black bean soup
directions: Rinse beans and place in a 6-quart stock pot.
Cover with water; bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Cover and set aside 1 hour.
Drain beans and return to stock pot.
Add ham hocks, water, celery salt and bouillon cube.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until beans are soft.
Remove ham hocks, coarsely chop meat and return it to the stock pot.
In another pan, saute onion, pepper and garlic in corn oil until limp.
Add these to the stock pot.
Add cumin seed, tomatoes, wine vinegar, wine, salsa and tomato sauce and simmer 45 minutes, uncovered. Add rice and simmer 15 minutes.
Correct seasoning with cayenne pepper, if desired, and if required, add potato flakes as a thickener.
Stir well.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Best served the next day to let flavors blend.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Beat potatoes and cream cheese in mixer bowl until smooth.
Add eggs, green onion and parsley; mix well.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish; dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chinese chews
directions: Blend well with hand.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar; add eggs and flavoring. Put vanilla wafer in paper cake cups, flat side down.
Fill cup 1/2 full of batter.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Cool and add fruit topping.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Stuff shells with mixture and arrange in 13 x 9-inch pan with sauce on bottom.
Add more sauce to cover top.
Top with additional Mozzarella cheese, if desired.

title: spanish rice(method:  one pot)
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
In large pot, brown hamburger, onion and green pepper, stirring continuously to crumble hamburger into small pieces.
Add tomatoes and water; heat to boiling. Remove from heat and add rice.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Serve hot, sprinkled with shredded cheese.

title: pepper steak oriental
directions: Brown garlic in oil in skillet. Cut meat into slivers of strips and place in bowl. Sprinkle with Kitchen Bouquet, salt and ginger.
Place meat in pan with onion and brown.
Add the green peppers, mushrooms and celery. Add 1/4 cup water and put cover on skillet. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and cooled chicken broth.
Add to contents in pan and bring to boiling. Serve over rice.

title: cucumber mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water adding grated onion.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water, then add to Jell-O.
Add the softened cream cheese to gelatin mix while hot whisking to blend.
Whisk in mayonnaise then Tabasco and salt.
Stir in grated cucumbers.
(Use only tender flesh; seeds and rind can be tough and bitter.)
Spray mold.
Pour mixture and allow to gel in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.

title: bacon and bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Cover and chill. Before serving, drain bean mixture.
Toss with bacon.
Top with eggs and sprinkle with paprika.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add enough pineapple juice to make a smooth paste.
Heat remaining juice; add to mixture.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add beaten eggs and butter.
Cook 1 or 2 minutes, stirring to prevent lumping; cool.
Fold in whipped cream before serving.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix ingredients and begin cooking.
After the butter melts, boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat until cool. Spread on cake.

title: wassail
directions: In large saucepan, heat cider and 1 cinnamon stick to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, uncovered.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except stars and cinnamon sticks.
Simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: fiesta swirls
directions: Combine cream cheese, chilies, olives, bacon, and salsa.
Mix well.
Spread on ovals of flat bread and roll up jelly-roll fashion starting with the longer side.
Refrigerate. When ready to plate, cut into 1/2 inch thick slices.

title: chicken stew
directions: In a large pan, heat oil and brown chicken.
Add wine.
Add leeks, celery, spices, onion and broth.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Skim off fat and remove onion.
Beat together the egg yolks and cream; gradually whisk into 1 cup of hot broth.
Stir in remaining broth. Heat through but do not boil.
Serve in bowls over brown rice with dark bread.

title: red pickle rings
directions: Cut cucumbers in rings.
Soak in lime in water for 24 hours.

title: spiced honey beef ribs
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place ribs in large container.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Place ribs on large baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours basting often and turning once.
Also great on the grill.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sharp cheese together.
Mix until well blended.
Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Mix well. Chill in refrigerator, then shape into ball. Roll in finely chopped pecans until ball is completely covered.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring in flour.
Drop by tablespoon in hot oil.
Cook until browned, turning over once. Drain.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, butter and milk in saucepan on medium heat. Let boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add vanilla, pecans and oats, stirring constantly.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: chicken dish
directions: Dip chicken in dressing and then in dry ingredients (use a bag to put crackers and cheese) and shake well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coffee bavarian
directions: Soften gelatin in the cold water in a large bowl.
Beat egg yolks and the whole egg with a fork in the top of a double boiler. Blend in the 2/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in the milk.
Dissolve coffee in the hot water and add to the egg-milk mixture.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until custard coats a spoon, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Do not overcook or custard will curdle.
Remove from heat and pour immediately over the softened gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved and stir frequently while the mixture is cooling.
When the mixture begins to stiffen, add the pinch of salt to the egg whites and beat until foamy.
Gradually add the 3 tablespoons sugar and continue beating until the egg whites are stiff and glossy.
Fold into custard mixture; turn into 1 1/2-quart mold and chill 4 to 6 hours.
Unmold and garnish with sliced peaches. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: st. paul rice
directions: Combine 4 1/2 cups water, soup mix and rice in saucepan.
Boil 7 minutes.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add beef, onion, green pepper and celery to soup mixture.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend milk and lemon juice.
Stir cherries, pecans and pineapple into milk and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Let cool for 2 hours.
Top with whip cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add grated zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to egg mixture. Add salt to mixture.
Fold in nuts or raisins, if desired.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pans (makes 2 loaves) after pans are sprayed or greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
This bread can be frozen after baking.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together; add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour and whipped cream together, then flavor.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press 1 can crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Spread on crescent rolls; add vegetables:
2 to 3 tablespoons minced onion, 1 carrot, grated, broccoli, cauliflower, tomato and cheese.

title: spinach delight
directions: Use whatever quantities you need.
Steam spinach and sliced or quartered mushrooms together until soft.
Just prior to serving, add sour cream (enough to coat).
Mix and serve hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave cheese at room temperature.
Then mix together with 1/4 cup walnuts.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into ball(s) (1 or 2) and roll in walnuts.
Garnish with 1/2 cherry, if desired.
Can be frozen.

title: stew(lapskaus)
directions: Simmer diced meat 1 hour.
When tender, add onion, potatoes and celery.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until vegetables are done and stew is thickened.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring
butter
and
water to a boil.
Add flour, all at once. Stir
and
cook
until
mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add an egg at a
time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Drop from a tablespoon 3 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 30
to
35 minutes
or until golden brown.
Remove from oven. Cut a
slit
in the
side
of
each.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 6 to 8 cream puffs.

title: (tomato) raspberry jam(from green or ripe tomatoes)
directions: Peel tomatoes; mash.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator or in freezer.
(Keeps 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip/mash potatoes.
Combine with sugar, eggs and 1 stick melted margarine.
Mix corn flakes, 1/2 stick melted margarine and pecans to make crumb mixture.
Place potato mixture in a greased casserole dish and sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix the cake mix and pistachio pudding together.
Push to side of the bowl, then add the other ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After the cake has cooled, cover with icing.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: salad squares
directions: Flatten crescent rolls on a cookie sheet, pressing seams together.
Bake according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing together.
Spread on cooled rolls. Using any combination of vegetables that you like, chop fine (use a food processor if you have one), then spread over dressing.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole dish and top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: green chili cornbread
directions: Chop chilies fine and grate cheese.
Preheat oven to 375°. Mix together the corn, slightly beaten eggs, oil and milk.
In separate bowl, mix the corn meal, soda and salt together.
Pour 1/2 the cornbread in 9-inch pan, then add chilies and cheese. Pour the rest of the mix over it.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: mock bailey's irish creme
directions: Pour all of the ingredients into a blender on high for 1 to 2 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, milk, flour and soda. Mix well.
Add apples.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased corn bread skillet. Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: grandma griffin's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, eggs and milk; add sugar and baking powder.
Slowly add flour until it makes soft mixture.
Roll out onto floured table.
Grandma rolled her dough out thick and used a 3 pound margarine lid to cut into large cookies.
You can use your favorite cookie cutters.
Bake in 325° oven until golden brown around edges.

title: chicken-asparagus divan
directions: Cook asparagus according to package directions.
Drain. Arrange in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir together soup, Worcestershire sauce and nutmeg; pour half over the asparagus. Sprinkle with 1/3 of the cheese.
Top with chicken and remaining soup mixture.
Sprinkle with other third of the cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Whip the cream just until soft peaks form; fold in mayonnaise.
Spread mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with remaining third of the cheese.
Broil 3 to 4-inches from the heat until topping is golden, 1 to 2 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased, covered, 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, 5 more minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper, green beans and half of the fried onions.
Put in 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining fried onions and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: rodeo round up pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs. Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together apples, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together brown sugar, rolled oats, flour and butter; crumble over apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crab, shrimp and cheese pastries
directions: Combine all ingredients except partries.
Roll out sheet pastry and stuff with all the ingredients, sealing the edges.
Bake in pre-heated 350° oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and 14 ounce white chocolate until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour into greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle M&M's over pizza.
Melt 2 ounces chocolate with oil.
Drizzle over pizza.
Chill.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place contents of vegetable seasoning package and butter in bowl.
Add hot water; stir to partially melt butter.
Add stuffing crumbs and stir gently to mix.
Cook frozen vegetables about 5 minutes in separate pan; drain.
Mix soup and milk in 2-quart casserole dish; stir in chicken and vegetables. Spoon stuffing over mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix cream cheese and
powdered	sugar.	Fold
in whipped cream to which 1/3 cup of
powdered
sugar
has been added.
If using Cool
Whip, do not add
sugar.
Spread
half
of
cheese mixture on top of baked, cooled crust.
Beat pudding with milk. Spread
on top of cream cheese
layer.
Spread
other	half
of cream cheese mixture on pudding	layer and garnish with crushed walnuts.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: meal in one casserole
directions: Press raw ground beef into bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cover with green beans; spread soup over this.
Cover top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned boiled egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in Pyrex bowl and put in pan of water.
Cook until firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together; pour over salad.
Chill and serve.

title: veggies casserole
directions: Arrange half of asparagus in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking
dish.
Combine
next
ingredients, stirring gently. Spoon
half this last mixture over asparagus.
Repeat layers. Combine
bread
crumbs
and
butter.
Sprinkle
over entire top. Bake,
uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until well heated.

title: marian's italian sausage lasagne
directions: Cook sausage, onion and garlic in skillet.
Brown and drain; set aside.
Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
In 6-quart pan, combine sausage mix and ground beef.
Stir in 2 tablespoons parsley, sugar, basil, mushrooms, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
