Bring to boil.
Reduce.
Simmer 45 minutes stirring frequently.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles and drain.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan, ungreased.

title: chicken salad(low-fat)
directions: Beat together both cream cheese.
Blend in chicken, celery and 2 teaspoons parsley.
Shape into a ball and sprinkle the top with almonds and remaining parsley.
Chill.
Serve with low-fat wheat crackers.
Serving size is 1 ounce with 90 calories and 6 g fat.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream
until smooth, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Using wax paper, shape into rolls about 2
x 10-inches.
This will make 2 rolls of cookie dough.
Wrap and
freeze.
When ready to bake, slice about 1/4 inch thick. Bake at
about 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: *moussaka 2
directions: Saute onions in butter. Add chopped meat.
Saute until red is gone. Add tomato paste, seasonings and wine. When well sauteed and moisture is absorbed, add grated cheese and mix.
Pare eggplant vertically in 4 long strips. Slice in 1/4-inch slices (circles). Salt and place in a colander to drain. Pat and place on paper towels. Saute briefly in lightly oiled pan.
Place on paper towels.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine meal and water in saucepan and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. May be lumpy.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, 1 at a time. Add cracker crumbs and soda, then pineapple, chopped nuts and coconut. This will seem real dry, but it won't be. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes without opening door. Let set and cool in pan.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, stir sauerkraut and its liquid, ginger and dressing. Spread out. Top with a layer of meat.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and place cheese on top of the meat in a single layer. Top with bread, lightly brushed with butter.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until bread is crisp. Makes 8 servings.

title: hash browns au gratin
directions: Place hash browns in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat onion, butter, soup and sour cream.
Spread over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Dot with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni, drain and rinse in cold water.
Pour 1/2 of shells in a deep casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 of tomato and meat sauce.
Spread 1/2 of sour cream over meat mixture.
Top with Provolone cheese.
Repeat, ending with the Mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake until cheese melts and browns.

title: lil smokies
directions: Cut each dinner roll into 4 equal pieces. Roll each fourth into a 5-inch rope. Dust with flour. Wrap each rope around each lil smokie several times and each ends under dough. Place on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: colonial pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Stir in pecans, raisins and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 300 degrees for about 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream when served or Cool Whip.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat; add chopped onions, sauce and seasonings.
Simmer while you cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine noodles, meat and sauce in well greased casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: t.n.t.
directions: Build in rock glass with cubed ice.

title: mexican cabbage(0 grams fat)
directions: Place sliced onions in bottom of bowl that can be baked in. Slice up cabbage over onions.
Pour tomatoes and chilies over cabbage.
Sprinkle salt and vinegar over all.
Cover and bake in microwave on Medium for 3 minutes, stir and cook 3 more minutes. Your microwave may take longer.
Ready to serve.

title: heath bar trifle
directions: Follow cake mix directions.
Cool and cut into small squares. Mix 3 boxes chocolate pudding with 4 1/2 cups milk.
Shaker Method: Shake vigorously at least 45 minutes or Beater or Mixer Method: Beat or mix until well blended, at least 1 to 2 minutes.
Crush candy bars into small pieces.
(Timesaver:
If you freeze candy bars first, it will be easier to crush.
If you have a food processor, you can throw in the frozen candy bars and have it crushed in no time!)
Layer as follows in a deep trifle bowl:
cake squares, chocolate pudding, Cool Whip and sprinkle crushed candy. Layer as many as your bowl will allow you!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray a 9-inch pie plate, then add the chicken, vegetables, soup, pepper and 1/4 cup milk.
In a small mixing bowl, mix the remaining milk, egg and baking mix. Pour over the chicken mixture and bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage in a large frypan; cook over medium heat until well done.
Sprinkle flour over sausage and fat.
Brown flour and then add milk.
Cook until thickened enough to serve over biscuits.

title: korean beef(bulgogi)
directions: Mix all ingredients except beef together.
Pour the mixture to beef and mix them well.
Keep them in a refrigerator for a couple of hours before cooking. Cook the beef in a pan or on
a grill.

title: dirty rice
directions: Add 3 tablespoons olive oil in large pot and fry beef and pork.
Stir in onion, bell pepper, celery and parsley; mix well. Add garlic, mint and cayenne pepper; mix well.
Add hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce and about 1 1/2 cups water and wine.
Add salt and stir well.
Let cook about 10 to 15 minutes, adding water as needed.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cooked rice, stir well to mix.
Cover and let simmer about 45 minutes.

title: baked fudge drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cocoa, milk, coconut, salt and vanilla in bowl.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: onion fried potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes into bowl.
Add soup mix and oil.
Toss until well covered.
Put mixture into baking dish.
Bake at
350° until potatoes are tender.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook 30 to 60 minutes or until thick.
Add 1/4 teaspoon basil and 1/4 teaspoon oregano.
Process in water bath 30 minutes. Makes 2 pints.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil pineapple and sugar.
Cool.
Mix pudding and milk.
Cool.
Whip heavy cream, vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Cool.
When cake is finished and cool, put crushed pineapple, sugar
and instant vanilla pudding on top of cake in layers.
Toast coconut and sprinkle on top.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine the Karo, sugar and water; boil until a little when tried in cold water forms a hard ball, 254°.
Add the vanilla and pour into the popped corn from which all hard grains should be removed.
Stir until coated.
Rub the hands with Mazola and form the corn into medium size balls, pressing closely together.
Let dry on waxed paper.

title: vidalia onions
directions: Cut 4 pieces of aluminum foil (enough to cover each onion). Clean onions and cut a hole in the top the size of a bouillon cube.
Place cube in onion top with a pat of butter or margarine and pour on Worcestershire sauce.
Bring the corners of the foil together and twist.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until onions are tender.
Serve with steaks, chops or any meal.
A real Southern tradition.

title: cranberry sparkle
directions: Blend well in a large bowl.
Garnish with citrus slices and ice.

title: turtles
directions: Cover 2 cookie sheets with buttered wax paper.
Arrange pecans in clusters about 1 inch apart.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese stand overnight to soften.
Mix cheese and sausage with hands.
Gradually add Bisquick; mix well.
Form into balls and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix crumbs with 3/4 stick margarine.
Spread and press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Whip together sugar, 1 1/2 sticks margarine and eggs.
Spread over crust.
Spread drained pineapple over filling.
Slice bananas and place over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Chill well.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Melt oleo and crush corn flakes or potato chips.
Mix well. Sprinkle on top and cook 10 minutes more, uncovered.

title: cherry salad
directions: Pour cherry Jell-O into hot water. Let stand 15 minutes.
Mix cherry filling, pineapple and Jell-O mix into a large bowl.
Add enough milk to make cream cheese soften.
Put sour cream in cream cheese. Mix very well.
Pour half the cherry mix in a large casserole.
Put in refrigerator to make firm.
Remove and spread cheese and sour cream mix onto cherry mix.
Sprinkle broken pecans, then pour cherry mix again.
Put casserole back into refrigerator to make firm.
Makes a very large salad.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over low heat until thick - stirring constantly.

title: coconut cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a skillet and add coconut, stirring constantly over low heat until golden brown.
Spread the coconut on an absorbent paper to cool.
Cream the other 2 tablespoons of margarine with cream cheese and add the milk.
Beat in the sugar gradually.
Blend in the vanilla and stir in 1 3/4 cups of coconut. Sprinkle remaining coconut on cake top.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Make cream sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Mix in hominy and chilies.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: barbecued pork chops(microwave)
directions: Lightly salt and pepper chops.
Combine flour, brown sugar and salt; coat chops with this mixture.
Arrange chops in greased glass dish.
Sprinkle remaining flour mixture over chops.
Top with onions, then pour barbecue sauce over all.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave 25 to 30 minutes, or until chops are tender. Turn chops four times during baking.

title: stromboli
directions: Defrost bread dough; spread dough on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Brush dough lightly with oil.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper, oregano and garlic salt.
Layer cheeses and meats on dough. Roll, tucking in ends.
Brush with oil.
Sprinkle with oregano. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, 10 to 15 minutes covered with foil. (Mine doesn't take quite that long.)
If reheating slice, bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Slice and serve.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Put undiluted soup in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in sherry, mushrooms, cooked crab and shrimp and raw scallops.
Toss gently. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Cook uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: cranberry cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Break up cranberries with a fork.
Stir cranberries, celery and walnuts into gelatin.
Fold in sour cream.
Mold; chill until firm.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix Beef with Onion, Egg, Salt, Pepper and Bread; mix well. Form into meatballs. Brown meatballs and drain. Add Soup and Water. Simmer for 10 minutes, while waiting for the Egg Noodles to cook.

title: chocolate chip glaze
directions: Heat ingredients.
Put in 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted.
Cook 5 minutes. Pour over cake.

title: wigglers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in pan.
Pour into roaster.
Add cooked potatoes, celery, carrots and spaghetti.
Pour mushroom soup over top.
Fry bacon and lay on top of this.
Pour tomato juice over everything.
Top with sliced cheese.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all but peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Bring to a boil. Then add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Spoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into molasses mixture.
Form in small balls, roll in granulated sugar and place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and 1/2 cup nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex to make crust.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool. Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on cooled crust. Mix together the pudding and milk.
Pour on top of cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: water chestnut hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut water chestnuts in halves or thirds and wrap bacon around. Fasten with toothpicks.
Bake on rack until browned.
Put in a shallow pan or casserole and bake 45 minutes in sauce made from brown sugar and catsup.
Serve hot or warm.
Makes about 40.

title: taco shells - soft
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Pour thin layer into 6 x 8-inch sprayed frying pan.
Turn once.

title: invisible ink
directions: Crush one Ex-Lax tablet thoroughly in alcohol.
"Paint on" with brush or Q-Tip.
Let dry.

title: oat bran, nuts, raisins and muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine flours and salt.
With blender at low speed, blend milk, eggs and butter or margarine.
Slowly add dry ingredients and process until smooth.
(Can be made ahead.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.)

title: chicken and rice with cheese
directions: Combine all; heat until hot and bubbly.

title: meatballs
directions: Break hamburg up in a large bowl.
Add salt, pepper, eggs, onion soup, Dutch rusk and water.
Mix well with hands.
Make into small meatballs.
Put in a small roaster or large baking dish. Heat chili sauce and grape jam together, then pour on top of meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; add caraway seed.
Work butter in dry ingredients until it feels like cornmeal.
Add egg to milk, mix well.
Add baking soda to milk mixture, will form bubbles.
Stir and add all at once to dry ingredients.
Mix with fork until well blended.
Dough will be sticky.
With floured hands, form into a ball.
Place in lightly buttered pie plate or cookie pan.
Flatten slightly, cut cross in dough 1/4-inch deep.
Sprinkle flour over top of loaf.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage; put in pan of boiling water.
Remove about 12 leaves when loose.
Mix hamburger, rice and tomato sauce in a large bowl.
Wrap hamburger ball in leaf of cabbage.
If it won't stay together, use toothpicks on stem of cabbage.
Put rest of ingredients in a large pot.
Put cabbage rolls in pot in 2 layers. Put lid on; simmer 3 hours or until cabbage is tender, about every 1/2 hour.
Remove grease formed on top of pot.

title: the best pie crust
directions: Blend pastry with a fork.

title: milk chocolate macadamia cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line buttered baking sheets with buttered waxed paper.
In a medium bowl, combine the flour and baking powder. In a large bowl, beat together the eggs, sugars, vanilla and almond extracts.
Add the flour mixture.
Stir in the milk chocolate chips and chopped Macadamia nuts.
Use 1 tablespoon dough for each cookie.
Drop them 1-inch apart on prepared baking sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Mix and put into 9-inch pie crust. Put on top crust and add slits to top crust. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Increase to 400° for 5 minutes. If using mixed vegetables, increase to 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If desired, add 1/2 cup slivered almonds.
Place in a greased 11 x 14-inch casserole. Sprinkle with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet-n-sour franks
directions: In pan combine syrup, juice, vinegar, cornstarch, Worcestershire and mustard.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in hot dogs and onions.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 8 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions. Slice potatoes and boil until tender. Heat soups together with a small amount of milk. Fix layers of meat, potatoes and cheese. Finish with cheese. Pour soup over top. Heat to blend flavors as long as needed. Can cook in crock-pot.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Add mayonnaise mixture to broccoli, onion and bacon; stir.
Add cheese last and stir gently.

title: beef stew
directions: Place bread in bottom of Dutch oven.
Mix remaining ingredients and place in Dutch oven. Cover tightly.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: feather buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add eggs.
Set aside.
Work sugar, salt and Crisco like pie crust.
Add 3 cups flour gradually.
Add egg mixture and work in remaining flour.
Cover with damp cloth. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out like pie crust. Cut into pie shaped wedges.
Roll up each wedge starting with large end.
Let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 24 medium size.

title: vegetable stew
directions: In large pot, melt 2 tablespoons Crisco and when heated, add chuck roast, onion and celery, then brown meat on both sides. Then add 5 cups water and simmer covered for 1 hour.
Afterwards, add all ingredients and cook for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally, adding water when needed.
When done, remove meat and cut into bite size pieces.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Mix egg in blender (or use mixer).
Add cottage cheese until smooth.
Add butter or oil and flour (or cornmeal).
Fry as you usually would for pancakes but make them smaller than usual.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on carton.
Drain.
Brown ground beef and add spaghetti sauce.
Mix Ricotta, cottage cheese and spinach.
In greased 9 x 13-inch dish, layer noodles.
Top with cheese and spinach mixture, then with Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with meat and sauce and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: filipino lumpias
directions: Brown meat; drain and let cool.
Chop onion and garlic; grate carrots.
Brown onion and garlic, then add carrots, cooking until crisp-tender.
Add meat to vegetable mixture.
Let cool. Separate wrappers and add about 2 tablespoons meat mixture to center of wrapper.
Roll up; seal with water on edges.
Deep fry until golden.
Makes a lot!
(You can freeze uncooked lumpias.)

title: oyster casserole
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Put 1/3 of mixture into small casserole.
Cover with half of the oysters.
Sprinkle with pepper and repeat.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1/4 cup oyster liquid.
Pour over oysters.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Place chopped dried beef in bottom of large baking dish. Arrange breast on top.
Combine all other ingredients; mix well. Pour over chicken.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Whip the evaporated milk until soft peaks form.
Mix water, lemon juice, gelatin and sugar and microwave for 1 minute on High. Stir the gelatin mixture into the whipped evaporated milk.
Add yellow food coloring.
Mix well with an electric mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips. Place in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.	Top with combined cheese and chips. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk dinner rolls
directions: Heat buttermilk and butter to 120°.
In large mixing bowl, combine 2 1/4 cups flour, sugar, yeast, egg and warmed buttermilk mixture.
Mix with dough mixer or by hand for 5 minutes.
Add 2 1/4 cups flour and continue kneading for 3 more minutes.
If sticky, knead enough of remaining 1/2 cup flour to form moderately stiff dough.
Place dough in greased bowl, turn once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled (1 hour).

title: cherry nut angel food cake
directions: Remove eggs from refrigerator; separate.
Let stand at room temperature.
Sift flour once before measuring.
Sift
together the flour and 3/4 cup of sugar 5 times.
In a large bowl, mix egg whites and salt.
Beat until foamy, about 1/2 minute.
Add cream of tartar.
Continue beating until whites are stiff and stand in points (not until dry).
Sprinkle in rapidly 1 cup sifted sugar. Beat 1 minute until blended.
Add extracts.
Sprinkle in sifted flour mixture evenly and quickly.
Beat only enough to blend, 1 1/2 minutes.
Cut up cherries and drain well on paper towel.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large skillet or pan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cool on wooden board or wax paper.
Knead.
When play dough is cooling, cover dough with moist paper towel.
Store in airtight container or Ziploc bag.

title: birdseed
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Serve in small cups. Disappears quickly!

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix pudding and jello mixes, then add water.
Cook until clear.
Fold in fruit.
Put into individual dishes or into a baked pie shell.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Stir ingredients well; pour in freezer.
Freeze until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Make a day ahead for best flavor.
Ice cream will be thick like Breyers.

title: pecan crunch pie
directions: Beat eggs and baking powder together until stiff.
Fold in graham crackers, pecans and vanilla.
Spread into buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break 1 loaf of bread into small balls and lay in pan.
Mix oleo, sugar, milk, pudding and cinnamon well.
Pour over bread balls.
Break the other loaf into balls and spread over the mixture.
Let rise until they are above the pan. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove skin and bones.
Chop it up.
Add small can of diced green chiles and cream of chicken soup.
In baking dish, layer torn up tortillas, mixture and cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squash relish
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cook fifteen minutes, then put in jars and seal.

title: creamed potatoes with parsley
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes into 1 to 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Boil until tender; drain off water.
Add 1 cup or more milk for sauce. Mix flour with water to thicken milk.
Add butter, salt, pepper and chopped parsley.

title: hot sauce
directions: Cook and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Process 10 minutes when it comes to a boil.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat in soda, salt, cinnamon and flour and mix well.

title: southern cabbage
directions: Place butter in an iron skillet and brown slightly.
Add shredded cabbage and stir well.
Cover tightly and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir again, cover and simmer for 5 minutes longer.
Add pepper, salt and cream and stir well.
Cover and simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: two minute fudge
directions: Stir and
blend the first five ingredients and place in a 1 1/2
quart dish.
Top this with the margarine.
Microwave on High for two minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in chopped nuts.
Pour into a wax-paper lined pan.

title: escargots bourguignonne
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix wine, parsley, butter, garlic, salt, pepper and onion in saucepan.
Heat.
Rinse and strain snails.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter or margarine until smooth. Blend in flour.
Divide into 24 balls.
Put one in each tin (muffin), pressing against side to line tin evenly.

title: never-fail divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and Karo in saucepan over high heat. Stir only until sugar dissolves.
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites in large mixer bowl until stiff on high speed.
Be sure bowl and beaters are grease free.
Cook syrup to 240°.
Pour about 1/2 of syrup over egg whites, beating constantly with mixer. Return syrup to high heat and cook to 265°.
Pour over mixture in bowl, beating constantly.
Do not scrape syrup pan.
Add vanilla and beat to mix.
Remove bowl from mixer and beat with wooden spoon until candy starts to lose gloss.
Stir in nuts and continue to beat until candy holds shape when dropped from spoon.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of pan.
Pour soup, cream cheese and sour cream over chicken.
Top with mixture of 1 1/2 cups Ritz cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: santa snacks
directions: Combine butter, graham cracker crumbs, coconut and spread in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Press lightly.
Cover with chocolate pieces.
Put nuts on evenly.
Pour on milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Heavily grease a Bundt pan and sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Add the batter and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Do not overbake.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, evaporated milk (reserve 1/3 cup) and melted margarine.
Press half of this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake for 10 or 12 minutes at 350°, then melt caramels in the remaining milk, sweet chocolate and pecans.
Remove first part of cake from oven and sprinkle chopped chocolate and chopped nuts on cake.
Pour melted caramel over this and put remainder of cake batter over top and return to oven and finish baking for 20 minutes more.

title: san antonio stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a large roasting pan and cook 1 hour on stove over medium heat.

title: buffet chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan; stir in flour, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes, stirring slowly; add chicken broth (stirring).
Cook until slightly thickened.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Add milk, onion, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Toss together.
Add beaten eggs.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Dot top with about 1 Tbsp. butter.
Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes.

title: crab omelets
directions: Saute vegetables in heavy skillet generously sprayed with Pam. Cook until soft, but not brown.
Cool.
Add to beaten eggs and seasonings.
Carefully fold in crabmeat.
When mixture is blended, drop 1/3 cup of mixture onto sprayed griddle or skillet.
Cook over medium heat until underside of omelet is lightly brown; turn carefully with a spatula and brown the other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve on hamburger buns with mayonnaise and/or ketchup, if desired.
Omelets freeze nicely.
Thaw and heat in microwave.

title: mock hollandaise sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, blend hot water with mayonnaise. Stir until heated through.
Add lemon juice and pour over vegetables.

title: angel hash
directions: Mix cornstarch in water.
Add to pineapple juice, sugar and egg yolk.
Cook until thickened.
Add pineapple and cool.
Whip the whipping cream until stiff.
Cut up other ingredients and add to the whipping cream.

title: onions for hamburger and steaks
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add onions and sugar.
Cook for 6 minutes, covered, on medium high heat and then cook 6 minutes uncovered.

title: key lime pie
directions: For Crust:
Melt butter and combine with graham cracker crumbs and brown sugar.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolk and combine with condensed milk.
Stir well and then add key lime juice and vanilla, stirring until blended.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely and refrigerate before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream before serving, if desired.
Yield: 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In medium size bowl, mix flour, salt and shortening until dough forms into small balls (the size of peas).
Then add water until it forms a a ball.
Roll out on a floured surface and put into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: gayle's 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well greased and floured jumbo fluted mold (such as a bundt pan).
Bake 1-1/2 to 1-3/4 hours at 325°.

title: lumberjack breakfast
directions: Crumble and brown the sausage; drain grease.
In a bowl whip eggs and milk; then add black pepper, red pepper and the Cheddar cheese.
Add to the sausage and cook together until eggs are done. Serve with biscuits.

title: slaw dressing for cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir or beat briefly with rotary beater to blend smooth. Mix into crisp shredded cabbage just before serving. Makes a generous cup of dressing.

title: yeast rolls
directions: If you want
fancy
shape
rolls, refrigerate overnight and shape to suit your fancy.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and put in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours, until chicken is well done. Remove chicken bones; cut chicken into chunks.
Strain broth into bowl. (Remainder of recipe may be cooked in crock-pot or on stove top, depending on available time.)

title: flan cake
directions: Blend ingredients for 4 minutes.
Put into flan pans, makes 2. Bake at 350°.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Top with any kind of pie filling or fresh fruit.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread out crescent roll dough and bake.
Mix together mayo, cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Pour over cooled crust.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Stir in sour cream.
Add sifted flour and soda 1/2 cup at a time.
Stir in extract and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.
Cool 5 minutes and turn onto rack to cool.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Boil tea bags in 2 cups water and pour over frozen juice in a large bowl.

Add sugar, bourbon and 8 cups water and stir until mixture is dissolved. Freeze overnight in large plastic storage containers. It scoops out into a slushy frozen treat to enjoy by itself or add a splash of Sprite to tone it down.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In saucepan, mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt together until blended.
Add hot water; cook over low heat until all ingredients are dissolved.
Add milk; cook until gravy boils and is thick.

title: fresh peach dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: stuffed baked potato
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bake potatoes.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop potato out of shells into bowl; mash.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Beat until light and fluffy. Spoon back into shells and place in 13 x 9-inch pan; top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is light golden brown.

title: smoky brisket
directions: Trim brisket.
Make a paste of all other ingredients except Worcestershire sauce.
Brush paste over brisket.
Wrap brisket in foil and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, open foil and spoon Worcestershire sauce over brisket.
Rewrap foil tightly and place in roasting pan.
Bake at 225° to 250° for 6 hours. Slice thin against the grain.
Keep warm in juices and serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, sugar, salt and shortening, cool until lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water and stir into mixture. Add eggs, stir in 4 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour and mix.
Let raise in greased bowl.
After mixture has risen, knead down and make out into round balls and let raise in greased pan.
Bake at 325° until done.
Brush butter over baked rolls.
This dough is good to keep in refrigerator before baking.

title: hazelnut cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Stir in nuts, flour and salt.
Roll in small balls and flatten slightly.
Bake 25 minutes in a 325° oven.
Take from cookie sheet while hot and roll in granulated sugar.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Whip cream cheese and preserves together.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: take along egg and macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill 2 hours.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles and vegetables according to package directions.
Add the soup, milk and tuna.
Bake 45 minutes in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Buttered crackers or bread crumbs may be put on as a topping before baking, if desired.

title: dry bean soup
directions: Put ham bone, pepper and water in a large pot.
Add beans and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add onion, carrots and celery leaves. Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add potatoes.
When potatoes are done, soup is ready to serve.
(Dry or split peas may be used instead of beans.)

title: lazy stuffed cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in large baking dish. Cook meat in skillet and drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over cabbage. Cover and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: beerrocks
directions: Saute onion and hot peppers until soft.
Add ground beef, salt and black pepper.
Brown meat.
Stir frequently.
Add chopped cabbage to meat mixture.
Keep stirring until cabbage looks cooked. Turn burner off.
Drain off fat.

title: orange baked yams
directions: Boil yams until tender in skins about 30 minutes.
Peel; cut in thick slices.
Arrange in buttered casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients; cook until thickened.
Pour over potatoes. Cover.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter; add soup.
Mix together.
Add 1/4 cup water if needed.
Combine chicken, noodles and pimentos with soup mixture.
Grate cheese; put on top.
Cook in oven until bubbly.

title: honey dressing
directions: In a medium size jar or blender, combine all ingredients. Shake or mix well.
Chill.
Serve over fresh greens or fruit salad.

title: barbecue smokies
directions: Make a large amount of laughter; add some tear drops mixed with sighs.
Add to this some sunshine and the smile of merry eyes. Put in two cups of morning dew diluting it with rain; stir it well with happiness but season it with pain.
Pour this in a golden cup buttered well with strife.
Wrap it around with problems; and this, my friend, is LIFE.

title: congo cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Melt shortening with sugar and cool before mixing with flour mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, chips and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured cake pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: coleslaw
directions: Prepare cabbage just before using. Shake together cream, vinegar and seasonings in covered jar.
Add this to cabbage just before serving, tossing slightly.

title: cheesy enchiladas
directions: In a saucepan, combine tomato sauce, water and enchilada seasoning mix; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown ground beef; drain.
Add 1 cup tomato sauce mixture to beef; simmer 5 minutes.
Soften tortillas, one at a time, in remaining sauce mixture.
Spoon beef mixture down center of each tortilla; sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Reserve 1/2 cup cheese and 2 tablespoons olives for garnish.
Roll up and place seam side down in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over top; sprinkle with reserved cheese and olives.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Or microwave, uncovered, on High 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taffy dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat at medium speed with mixer until smooth.
Serve with fruit slices.
It's a great way to get the kids to eat their fruit.

title: mother's fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together good.
Put back into graham cracker wrapper and chill overnight before cutting.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter in casserole dish. Add both cans of corn, corn meal mix and sour cream. Mix well. Bake for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, cocoa, flour and vanilla with about 1/4 cup milk until mixed well.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour in crust and top with egg whites.
Beat egg whites with dash of salt and 1 teaspoon cold water until stiff.

title: "broccoli corn bread"
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish at 350° to 400°.
If desired, grate cheese on top just before casserole is done.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, combine frozen corn, potato, onion, water, bouillon granules and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until potato is tender.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of milk and the margarine.
Combine remaining milk and flour.
Stir milk-flour mix into corn mix.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Prepare the Rice-A-Roni, omitting the butter.
Slice the onion very thinly and separate into rings.
Thinly slice the olives. Slice/shred the artichoke hearts, reserving the juice.
Add sliced vegetables to the rice mixture.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Chop the pears into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Don't add any water to this cake; the pears and oil will give enough moisture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until testing in center.

title: vicki's mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and
boil
10 medium size potatoes for 20 minutes. Drain. Beat
with mixer until smooth.
Add milk, butter, then cream cheese
(softened)
and sour cream.
Mix, then add salt, pepper and 3 shakes of garlic salt.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350°
for
45 minutes (covered).
Men love this dish. Can be made ahead and put in fridge until ready to bake.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
For variety, add chopped nuts, raisins, chocolate chips or coconut.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: sponge cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
May sprinkle with coconut or may add chocolate bits. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: Brown bacon lightly.
Add onion and green pepper; cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until onion is golden.
Remove from heat.
Add beans, bean stock and salt.
Simmer until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Serve hot.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: valentine salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with sugar and mayonnaise.
Stir in fruits and marshmallows, then whipped cream.
Pour into heart shaped mold.
Freeze at least 6 hours.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix all together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "baptist" chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
After chicken has been stewed, remove the bones and skin.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and put in the bottom of of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour the can of soup over the chicken.
In a separate bowl, mix together the stuffing, broth and melted margarine.
Spread this mixture over the chicken and soup.
Pour milk evenly over the stuffing mix. Cover casserole dish with foil paper and bake for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.
Remove foil paper and bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mary's cornbread dressing
directions: Boil chicken with the livers, green onions, celery and green pepper.
Bake cornbread according to package directions.
Crumble baked cornbread, add deboned chicken, boiled eggs, chopped chicken livers, green onion, green pepper and celery.
Mix soups full strength to mixture, pour in chicken broth and mix well.
Season to taste.
Do not mix too dry.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt oleo and brown sugar in a small pan and let cool.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer.
Take out and let cool.
Cut into squares.
They will be a little sticky but good.

title: orange tea quencher
directions: In a 2 quart pitcher, combine tea, water, orange juice, lime juice and Sugar
Twin.
Mix
well.	Add
club soda.
Pour into ice-filled tall glasses.
Garnish each with slice of lime before serving.
Serves 4.

title: spice nuts
directions: Pour on wax paper.
Cool.
Break
into pieces. Store in tin or airtight container.

title: chili-rice dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; add spices, corn, peppers, tomatoes and water.
Cover and bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat.
Cover and let simmer 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Layer chicken breasts, boiled ham and Swiss cheese.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over chicken layers.
Melt butter and mix with croutons.
Put croutons on each breast.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: snappy bites
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.
Freezes well.

title: hoe-cakes
directions: Combine meal, flour, salt and sugar.
Add buttermilk to make batter right consistency to fry.
Have griddle or skillet hot with plenty of shortening.
Fry until golden brown on both sides as you would for pancakes.
Serve hot with butter.

title: kentucky fried corn
directions: Lightly fry bacon, mix other ingredients thoroughly; pour into bacon grease.
Fry slowly so as not to brown too quickly, about 25 minutes.

title: mother's baked rice dish
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir occasionally.
Leave uncovered to make rice crisp on top.
Serves 6.

title: savory rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and microwave on High power for 3 to 5 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar and boiling water.
Mix and add orange juice, pineapple and bananas in lemon juice.
Mix together and freeze. Stir 3 or 4 times while freezing.
Take out about half hour before serving.

title: pet meat loaf
directions: Mix well all ingredients and shape into a loaf in a shallow baking pan.
Pour 1 cup hot water around loaf.
Put 3 to 4 teaspoons of butter on top, then add rolled cracker crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: cornbread sticks
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Heat greased iron pans until hot enough to sizzle. Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Yields 14 servings.
Preparation time is 30 minutes.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Soak yeast in 1/2 cup water for 5 minutes.
Combine milk, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl; stir to dissolve.
Beat in shortening, eggs, yeast mixture and 1 cup flour; mix until smooth. Add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, and mix until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead until dough becomes smooth, elastic and no longer sticky, using flour as needed.
Place in lightly greased bowl; grease top lightly, cover and let rise in warm place until double in size (1 to 1 1/2 hours for each time you raise it).
Divide into desired shapes and rise and bake.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts and freeze.
Serve with chocolate syrup.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat until foamy.
Sift flour and soda; add and blend well.
Add nuts and mix.

title: peanut pudding dessert
directions: Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with a few peanuts.

title: 1-2-3 dessert
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, pineapple and dry pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix cheese until smooth. Gradually add sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip; blend well. Spoon into crust. Chill until set.

title: french market soup
directions: Sort and wash soup mix; place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above soup mix; let soak 8 hours.

title: my chicken divan
directions: Precook chicken and broccoli separately.
Spread broccoli in a casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
In separate bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, confectioners sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and salt. Divide dough in half; blend food color into one half.
Shape 1 teaspoon dough from each half into 4-inch rope.
For smooth, even ropes, roll them back and forth on lightly floured board.
Place ropes side by side, press together lightly and twist.
Complete cookies one at a time.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; curve top of cookie down to form handle of cane.
Bake about 9 minutes or until set and very light brown.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in shrimp. Cook on medium heat until shrimp are done, 10 to 15 minutes. Add a small amount of water as needed.
Add green onions; cook about 5 minutes. Season with salt and peppers.
Serve over rice.

title: nancy grifo's easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Add basil, oregano, salt, pepper, garlic powder and parsley to taste.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Add carrot and simmer approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheeses (Mozzarella, Velveeta and Parmesan).
End in the cheese layer.
Cook 30 minutes and check to see if it needs more water.
Cook another 30 minutes. (Total time 1 hour at 350°.)

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain off fat.
Add milk, cheese and macaroni as well as other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate caramel sheet cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed. Bake on greased and floured sheet cake pan or cookie sheet pan as directed.

title: cinnamon strips
directions: Mix sugar with cinnamon.
Toast the bread.
Butter both sides of the toast and cut into thin strips.
Pour the sugar-cinnamon mixture into the plastic bag.
Seal tightly and shake to mix well. Drop 1 strip of buttered toast into the bag and shake until the strip is coated.
Repeat until all the toast strips have been coated.
Add more sugar-cinnamon mix if you need it.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook hamburg with taco seasoning per package directions.
Mix in refried beans.
Pour mixture into rectangular baking dish. Pour on jalapeno cheese dip and spread evenly.
Layer salsa, lettuce, peppers and olives, in whatever order you choose, ending with a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Dip will be hot, medium or mild depending on what taco seasoning and salsa you choose.

title: easy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and sugar in saucepan; cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pecans.
Place graham crackers on cookie sheets, side by side so icing won't come off in pan and scorch.
Spread icing on crackers and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.
Break into small bars along indentation on back of crackers as a guide.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except shortening and soup.
Form meatballs and brown in shortening.
Place in dripper.
Mix soup with fork until creamy and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: aunt jan's swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into both sides of meat, using back side of knife. Add tomato puree, water, salt and pepper.
Pressure cook at 10 pounds for 25 to 30 minutes.
Twelve minutes before serving, add pepper, potatoes, carrots and onions.
Pressure at 15 pounds for 12 minutes.
If gravy is thin, add a little flour and cold water, mixed into paste, with a fork.

title: forever coleslaw
directions: Finely chop first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Then pour over slaw.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix baking soda in water and pour over dates. Let soda, water and dates set for about 20 minutes. Add butter, sugar and egg. Add flour, nuts and vanilla and mix well. Add this to date mixture. Mix all together. Beat and pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 375 degrees for 40 minutes. Cover with Brown sauce.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Blend in flour and salt.
Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until edges are brown.
Pour chocolate chips on top and let them melt.
Spread like frosting. Cut and enjoy.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix with crumbs.
Line 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with 1/2 crumb mixture.
Mix seafood with 2 cans Campbell's shrimp soup (undiluted) and 1/2 cup Miracle Whip.
Pour into dish and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes a large dish.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs, molasses and soda until foamy.
Add sugar and other ingredients and beat. Add water (boiling) last.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: soft rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in sour cream.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Chill dough. Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Frost, if desired.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Grease a jelly roll pan.
Open up crescent rolls and spread out on pan, pressing together to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix Miracle Whip, cream cheese and Hidden Valley Ranch mix together until creamy.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle veggies over spread, pressing down slightly.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Chill; cut into small squares.
Keep chilled.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape in small balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: curried rice
directions: In a 2-quart pan, cook onion, celery and curry powder in butter or margarine until celery is tender, not brown.
Add rice, stir in bouillon, water and salt.
Cover and boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is done.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes.

title: pickled eggs(2 quart jars)
directions: Bring peppers,	pepper	juice,	vinegar
and
salt to a boil. Layer carrot sticks, onions, peppers and eggs in jar to the top of jar.
Pour liquid mixture over contents in the jar. Cover and let stand
3 to 7 days.
(Gets hotter the longer it stands.)

title: herbed pea salad
directions: Place nuts in small baking, roast at 350° for 10 minutes. Put nuts in kitchen towel and rub together to remove skins. Chop coarsely.

title: (no bake) cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Put in baked pie crusts. Cover with cherry, peach, apple, strawberry or blueberry pie filling and chill.

title: meat balls
directions: Make into balls the rice, meat and milk.
Add soup and bake 1 hour.

title: pork chop and vegetable dinner
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Place over heat until hot.
Add pork chops and brown on each side.
Layer sweet potato, squash and pineapple over pork chops.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, brown sugar and next 2 ingredients.
Stir well and pour over pineapple.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add apple slices, cover and cook an additional 5 minutes.

title: all in one breakfast
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Brown and crumble sausage or bacon. In a 9 x 12-inch pan sprayed with Pam, layer bread, meat and then cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and mustard.
Pour over top. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 soup can of milk.
Pour over top.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: tomato-topped chicken and stuffing
directions: Crush 1/2 cup stuffing.
In small bowl, combine crushed stuffing and margarine.
Set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining stuffing; toss to mix well.
In small bowl, combine soup and milk. Spoon 1/3 cup soup mixture into 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Top with stuffing.
Arrange chicken on stuffing.
Spoon remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Top with tomato.
Sprinkle with reserved stuffing mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Makes 6 servings.

title: black-eyed pea jambalaya
directions: Put all ingredients in rice cooker; stir and cook.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in buttermilk.
Cut shortening into flour mixture, then stir in buttermilk quickly. Knead until smooth and roll very thin.
Cut and place one on top of another.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tayglach
directions: Mix together flour, salt and cinnamon.
Add egg to form dough. Roll into thin ropes.
Cut into 1/4-inch long pieces.
Bring honey to a boil in a small pan.
Add Tayglach a few at a time. Boil slowly until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Spoon into a dish and cool.
Pour remaining honey over Tayglach when ready to serve.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs.
Cut eggs in half.
Mix yolks with rest of ingredients.
Spoon into center of halved eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in a pan over low heat. Stir only until sugar is dissolved. Cook until soft ball forms in cold water. Beat egg whites 2 minutes at high speed until stiff. Continue beating and pour half of the mixture slowly over the beaten egg whites.
Keep cooking the syrup mixture until a hard ball forms in cold water.
Mix in the other half of the mixture. Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour in a glass 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs and beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: jackson cake
directions: Add to the above.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Double time if you double recipe.
(Double all ingredients for oblong cake pan.)
Ice while hot.

title: potato cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together with hands.
Roll into balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: tuna tomato bake
directions: Place onions and celery in 2-quart casserole dish in oil. Cook 3 to 4 minutes (until tender).
Blend in remaining ingredients; top with croutons.
Cook in oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until heated through.

title: children's strawberry punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, dissolve the Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Add a cup of the sugar and stir until dissolved. Add the orange juice and the lemonade, prepared according to directions on the cans.
Pour in the pineapple juice. Stir in the remaining cup of sugar and mix well.
Just before serving the punch, add the ginger ale and some ice cubes.
Makes about 30 cups.
Floating orange slices makes a pretty garnish or put a cherry and the orange slices on a toothpick.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, chocolate and cream of tartar in large bowl.
Add egg yolks (slightly beaten), margarine and vanilla; mix well, then add milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: jelly roll
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar, then add water.
Add sifted ingredients.
Beat all together until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured, shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: egg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, adding mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Refrigerate.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in a 1 3/4-quart saucepan.
Add onion.
Cook over low heat.
Stir; sprinkle with flour; cook and stir 2 minutes. Add bouillon and simmer gently for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Float toast on soup (in individual crocks), sprinkle with cheese and place crocks under broiler until cheese is lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Place 30 x 18-inch piece heavy-duty foil in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place meat on foil, sprinkle with dry soup mix over top of meat and spread with cream of mushroom soup.
Fold foil over meat and seal securely.
Bake at 325° for 4 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients except sour cream. Fold in sour cream.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Blend
shortening,
peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Shape in balls. Press
to
flatten	slightly on baking sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and press a candy kiss on each cookie.

title: marinated salad
directions: Bring the last 4 ingredients to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain off excess water.
Mix together spinach, sour cream, onion, mayo and vegetable soup mix.
Chill for 2 hours. Cut out the center of a big, round loaf of bread and fill the hole with dip.
Serve with cut out bread, crackers and raw vegetables.

title: cranberry grape salad
directions: Combine cranberries, apples and sugar; set aside.

title: lemon-dill sauce for grilled fish steaks
directions: In skillet, saute garlic in butter.
Add olive oil and heat; do not burn butter and garlic.
Mix in dill, stirring over medium heat.
Stir in white wine.
Stir in lemon juice.
Baste fish steaks plentifully during grilling.
Leftover baste can be served on steaks when served.
Great on salmon, swordfish and king fish.

title: cheesy brat stew
directions: In a 3-quart buttered casserole, stir together the sausage, potatoes, green beans, soup, cheese and onion.
Bake casserole, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until heated through. Serves 8.

title: split pea soup
directions: Saute bacon until lightly browned. Add onion, ham, carrot, and celery. Continue to cook until bacon is fully cooked. Pick over peas and discard bad ones. Rinse under running water. Add to bacon mixture. Add water, pepper sauce, worcestershire, ham base, and minced garlic.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil, dressing mix and garlic salt in large bowl.
Add crackers.
Stir gently every 15 minutes for 2 hours.
Store in tightly covered container.
These will keep for a long time.

title: raisin pineapple drops
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla together until light and fluffy. Add egg and beat well.

Stir in raisins and pineapple. Sift together dry ingredients and add gradually to creamed mixture, stirring until well blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: sweet-sour beef 'n cabbage
directions: In a pan, cook hamburger, onions, celery and peppers until brown.
Drain fat.
Sprinkle meat mixture with oats, parsley, salt, garlic and pepper.
Core cabbage and cut into wedges.
Place on meat.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips, peanut butter and marshmallows in top of double boiler.
Add noodles.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased wax paper.
Cool.

title: praline pumpkin mousse pie
directions: Soften gelatin in praline liqueur and set aside.
Heat pumpkin, yolks, brown sugar, sugar, butter, cinnamon, salt and cloves in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until slightly boiling and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Beat in gelatin mixture until gelatin is dissolved (about 1 minute).

title: grandma's refrigerator oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add alternately with rest of dry ingredients.
Add nuts, raisins and oatmeal (and chocolate morsels).
Shape in rolls; wrap in wax paper and put in refrigerator.
(Or drop teaspoonful at a time on cookie sheet if baking immediately.)
If in refrigerator, slice and bake as desired in medium oven, 350°, until desired consistency, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients by hand, then fold in nuts.
Run a knife through the apple slices and fold into cake.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes. Combine powdered sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add enough milk to make a glaze.
Pour over cake.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In heavy, 2-quart saucepan, melt butter. Meanwhile, on piece of waxed paper, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken in melted butter.
Roll in crumbs to coat.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Sift flour with soda, cinnamon nutmeg, allspice and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Then add nuts and prunes.
Pour into greased and floured 13x9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until tests done.
While cake is still hot, ice with Buttermilk Icing.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Dissolve baking soda in the pineapple and add with rest of ingredients to dry mixture.
Bake in a bread pan at 350° for about an hour, or until it tests done.
Cool on rack; wrap in plastic and store in refrigerator.
This will keep for a long time.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in frypan.
Fill pan with water 1/4 inch deep. Add lemon juice.
Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes each side. Remove chicken and cut into cubes.

title: potato fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together then add to potatoes.
Add vanilla, mix in 10 x sugar then nuts.
Spread in an 8 inch square pan (buttered lightly).
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger, onions and green pepper together.
Mix ketchup or barbecue sauce, sugar, honey, applesauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with cooked meat and onions.
Add bacon.
Stir all of the ingredients into beans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°. This recipe fills 1 bean pot.

title: golden bananas
directions: Cut bananas into halves lengthwise and halves widthways. Place in a casserole dish, cover with demerara sugar and lemon juice.
Cover dish with lid and bake in oven at 400° or on gas mark 4 for 30 minutes.
Serve with cream.

title: creamy vanilla frosting
directions: Shake flour and milk in a jar.
Pour in a saucepan and cook till thick.
Cool.
Texture will be like paste.

title: italian spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Rinse well.
Toss all ingredients together.
This is better if made ahead of time. Makes a large bowl.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, salt, syrup, oleo and cream of tartar.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, then add baking soda.
Pour over popped corn and mix thoroughly.
Bake on cookie sheet for 1 hour at 200°.
Stir occasionally while baking.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix meal, flour and sugar well.
Add egg.
Mix with buttermilk.
Heat oil in pan.
Pour into mix.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: stuffed beef rolls
directions: Combine eggs, ground beef and salt.
Combine bread crumbs, onion, sage, salt and pepper.
Add water.
Divide meat into 8 portions.
On waxed paper, pat each into 4-inch square.
Top with 2 tablespoons crumb mixture.
Roll up and seal.
Make 8 rolls. Coat with flour.
Brown in hot oil.
Remove and drain off fat.
In skillet, bring to boil mushroom soup, pimento and water.
Add meat rolls and sliced mushrooms.
Reduce heat and cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fried fish
directions: Make batter of Bisquick and 7-Up; dip fillets in batter and fry at 350° in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, Crisco, salt and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve the soda in the buttermilk; add alternately with the flour.
Add the coconut and chopped nuts. Bake for 25 minutes at 350° in 3 (8-inch) pans.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients until very smooth.
Fold in third ingredient until mix becomes creamy.
Pour in crust and chill until set.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate milk and flour; blend well.
Add flavorings. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie with buttermilk
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Add margarine, beaten egg yolks, vanilla, coconut and buttermilk. Pour into pie crust. Set aside 3 egg whites for top. Brush 1 egg white on pie crust. Bake at 300 degrees for about 1 hour or until brown and set. Beat egg whites until stiff and stir in 3 Tbsp. sugar. Spread on top of baked pie and return to 300 degree oven and bake 15 minutes or until brown.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine ingredients and put into greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat filling for manicotti
directions: Brown meat with Italian seasoning and salt, stirring to break into small pieces.
Drain.
Mix cheese, bread crumbs and spaghetti sauce thoroughly through meat.
Stuff shells same as cheese manicotti.
Makes 14 shells.

title: chopped liver molds(duck shaped)
directions: Broil liver or saute with onions in chicken fat.
Grind liver, cooked onion and hard-boiled eggs until fine.
Season.
Use enough water to give a consistency which will be moldable.

title: thick vegetable soup
directions: May also add 1 package romaine noodles and additional spices (basil, parsley).

title: jam cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and wet ingredients separately.
Add together.
Beat at low speed. Cook at 300° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Let set in covered dish for two days.
Jam will soak into cake.
Slice and eat.
No icing required.

title: grandma's creamed onions
directions: Cook onions in boiling, salted water covered 20 to 25 minutes. Drain and reserve 1/2 of liquid.

title: baked mushroom rice
directions: Place rice in lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1/2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook green onions in butter in large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add broth and remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Remove from the heat and pour over rice.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender; stir before serving.

title: grandma's cinnamon flop
directions: Sift sugar, flour and baking powder together. Add butter and milk and blend. Divide into two 9-inch cake pans that are greased. Sprinkle tops with flour, then brown sugar and then cinnamon. Push chunks of butter into the dough. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into wedges and serve warm with hot chocolate after a day in the snow.

title: pumpkin bread(yields 3 loaves)
directions: Blend together on low speed sugar, oil and eggs.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Slowly mix into sugar mixture.
Add pumpkin and water alternately. Grease 3 loaf pans and divide evenly.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon gems
directions: In bowl combine 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon rind. With pastry blender, cut butter into dry ingredients until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Pat crumbs evenly into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake until lightly browned at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour, milk, soda and eggs well, then add mashed bananas and chopped nuts.
Bake in greased dish for 1 hour on 350°.

title: mother kibbes' pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add milk to obtain right consistency. Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 1 hour at 425°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: easy tortilla bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet brown beef and drain. Add chili and sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Dip quartered corn tortillas in sour cream.
In a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, place 1/2 of tortillas to line bottom.
Top with 1/2 of meat, 1/2 of onion and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: raisin apple muffins
directions: Grease or line 12 muffin cups.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Combine butter, milk, egg, vanilla and apple.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.
Bake at 400° in upper third of oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: ice cream
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine condensed milk, eggs, sugar and 4 cups whole milk; beat well before putting on the heat.
Over medium heat, cook like custard; remove from heat and cool.
Add cream and flavorings.
Pour mixture into ice cream maker; pour in additional whole milk to the fill line.
Freeze in usual manner.

title: strawberry chiffon
directions: Mix gelatin and 2 cups boiling water; set aside 1/4 cup of gelatin mixture.
To
remaining
gelatin, add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Refrigerate for 1 1/2
hours.
Combine softened cream cheese, whipped topping, vanilla, confectioners sugar, nuts and the remaining 1/4 cup gelatin;
mix until well blended.
Frost gelatin.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: flora otwell's punch
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.

title: freezer lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add Ragu spaghetti sauce and simmer over medium heat.
Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella, egg, parsley, salt and pepper.
Layer in the following order in two 11 x 13-inch pans (good size so it doesn't cook over in oven): meat sauce, noodles, cheese mixture, then repeat layers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine on stove.
Add 2 cups sweet potatoes, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Remove from stove. Add eggs and milk; mix, then put into pie shells.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: four cheese stuffed shells
directions: Beat egg lightly in bowl.
Stir in parsley, salt, nutmeg and pepper until blended.
Stir in cheeses until thoroughly combined. Stir in heavy cream.
Fill cooked shells.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly hot.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Cook hamburger and onion; drain.
Add the sauce/meat with mushrooms; simmer for 15 minutes. Layer sauce mix, noodles and cheeses in crock-pot.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook and remove chicken from bone.
Put in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put broth and soup in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken and eggs.
Combine melted margarine, pepper, flour and milk; mix to form batter.
Pour and spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, corn syrup and water in a deep 2-quart bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on Full power for 4 minutes. Stir.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes, stirring the last few minutes. Stir in vanilla.
Pour onto ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over toffee and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate together; cool.
Beat eggs; add sugar and beat until thick.
Add vanilla and chocolate.
Add flour; stir until just blended.
Bake in well-greased 9-inch square pan at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until it strings.
Then pour in raw peanuts and cook until sugar browns.
Rapidly pour in soda as taken from stove.

title: pennsylvania dutch cole slaw
directions: Shred
the
cabbage
and peppers.
Put in a large bowl. Add the sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Press with the hands until all the juices are blended.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine onion soup mix with bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in bread crumb mixture, coating well.
Place in a lightly greased, large, shallow baking pan and drizzle with butter.
Bake, turning once, 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes about 2 dozen nuggets.

title: joyce's big salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup juice and 1 3/4 cups cold water.
Add celery, pecans, carrots, cottage cheese and drained pineapple.
Mix well and place in refrigerator until congealed.
Top with salad dressing.
Serves many!

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir and let set in pot for 1 hour.
Pour into other container and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
It will thicken as it cools.

title: layered vegetable casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Layer squash, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, mushrooms, remaining Mozzarella and spinach in casserole.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Save some coconut to sprinkle on top.
Blend potatoes, butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy chicken
directions: Lay chicken in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Mix together onion soup mix, cranberry sauce, dressing and water.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken chip casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish, except the potato chips.
Crush chips and mix half of the bag in the casserole dish.
Sprinkle the rest of the chips on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
The top of the casserole will be crunchy if you don't cover the dish.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Stir over low heat. Beat with rotary beater.
Makes 5 cups.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin and oil together.
Then in another bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon, then add to above and mix.
Grease 9 x 14-inch flat cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, or until done.

title: microwave italian zucchini(zuke those zucchini)
directions: Place zucchini and next 5 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole. Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 13 to 16 minutes until zucchini is crisp-tender, stirring once.
Ladle into bowls; sprinkle with evenly divided Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Bake potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel and grate. Combine potatoes with sour cream, 1 cup cheese, carrot, onion, parsley, salt, dill and pepper.
Turn into buttered, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Fry bacon crisp; crumble into pie shells.
Beat eggs, cream and seasoning together.
Stir in cheese.
Pour equal amounts into pie shells.
Bake at 325° until top is golden brown, about 35 minutes.
You may substitute with ham instead of bacon if you wish.

title: grilled venison ribs(serves 4)
directions: Combine ketchup, chili sauce, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, black pepper, hot sauce and onion into bowl. Mix well.
Refrigerate until needed. Cut ribs in half.
Place into a stock pot, along with liquid smoke.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer.
Cook until tender (about 1 hour).
Then place ribs over medium hot coals.
Turn often until slightly brown.
Brush both sides until sauce is gone (about 30 minutes).

title: citrus honey peas
directions: Saute rinds in butter in skillet.
Stir in juices and honey. Boil until thickened.
Stir in peas and pimentos.
Heat to serving temperature.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrot in margarine for 10 minutes. Add flour to mixture and stir.
Cook 1 minute.
Combine broth and milk.
Stir into flour mixture and cook until thick.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Add chicken.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with pastry and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix fruit juices with cold water.
Pour over ice cubes in punch bowl.
Add chilled ginger ale.
Garnish with twisted lime slices. Serves 60.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage and drain on paper towel.
Sift biscuit mix.
Add sausage and grated cheese.
Mix well and form into small balls. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, varying according to ovens.

title: veggie quesadillas
directions: Combine salsa, beans, and zucchini.
Spread 1/4 of the mixture over each of 4 tortillas.
top each portion with 3 tablespoons cheese; cover each with another tortilla.
Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat.
One at a time, carefully cook each quesadilla, turning once, until cheese is melted, about 1 minute on each side.
Cut each quesadilla into quarters; serve immediately.

title: chicken scaloppine with orange sauce
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of wax paper and pound firmly with a meat mallet or rolling pin until they are 1/4-inch thick or thinner.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; dip in flour and pat briskly to remove excess.

title: pinwheels
directions: Spray an 8 or 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray. Mix gelatin and water in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart bowl; microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes, stir to dissolve completely.
Add marshmallows, microwave 1 minute.
Stir mixture slowly until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour into prepared pan. Refrigerate 45 minutes or until set.
Loosen edges with knife. Starting at one edge, roll up tightly.
With seam side down, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 pieces.

title: cranberry apple crunch
directions: Combine first four ingredients and put in greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Combine rest of ingredients and spoon over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken with marsala wine over penne
directions: Melt butter until sizzling, then add oil.
Dredge cutlets in flour and immediately place into frypan.
Cook on high until golden, 2 1/2 to 3 minutes per side.
Remove cutlets.
Set aside to drain fat.
Place shallots into pan and saute 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms, chicken broth and Marsala cooking wine.
Cook 2 minutes. Add cutlets.
Turn off.
Cook pasta.
