Drain pasta; place into a large bowl and pour chicken and liquid over pasta.
Enjoy!

title: holiday chicken dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients shortly before baking.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch flat Pyrex dish for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: oatmeal krispies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets; remove to wire racks.
Yield: about 8 dozen.

title: texas millionaires(short cut)
directions: Melt the caramel candy, water and butter in a double boiler. Add pecans.
Drop on tray and cool.
Melt chocolate bar and paraffin in double boiler; mix until smooth.
Dip caramel patties in chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown meat (drain). Add other ingredients. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes (good and fast). Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Slowly brown pecans in oleo.
Set aside.
Cook eggs slowly with pudding mix, sugar and a small amount of milk.
Add flavorings and Eagle Brand milk and other milk or cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into freezer container.
Add enough milk to fill to line.
Add pecans and freeze.

title: best bean salad ever
directions: Mix in large bowl salt, pepper, vinegar, sugar and vegetable oil.
Mix until sugar is dissolved; then pour over vegetables (onion, green pepper, green beans, yellow wax beans, red kidney beans, baby lima beans).
Let set 12 hours or overnight (the longer the better).

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients 1 at a time in order given.
Bake 30 minutes; cool for 30 minutes in pan, then cut into squares. (These are very rich, so cut small!)

title: chocolate peanut butter bites
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with foil; set aside.
In medium mixing bowl, combine peanut butter, 2 tablespoons butter Crisco, graham cracker crumbs and confectioners sugar.
Mix well; mixture will be stiff.
Set aside.
In double boiler or small saucepan over very low heat, melt chocolate chips and remaining 2 tablespoons butter Crisco, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Pour half the melted chocolate mixture into prepared pie plate.
Spread chocolate about 1/2 inch up sides of pie plate.
Place in freezer for about 10 minutes, or until set.
Remove from freezer.
Spread peanut butter mixture over set chocolate.
Pour remaining melted chocolate over peanut butter layer, spreading to edges.
Place in freezer or refrigerator to set.
Cut or break into bite size pieces.

title: peanut butter crinkle cookies
directions: In bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat first 6 ingredients until fluffy.
At low speed, beat in next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Immediately press Hershey's Kisses or pecans into cookies.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: barbecue sandwich filling
directions: Taken from the Burnett Book of Household Receipts, printed 1886, fifth edition.

title: broccoli-rice
directions: Mix rice and broccoli; stir in half Cheez Whiz.
Melt oleo and cook onions and celery.
Stir in soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and rice.
Put rest of Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown a large chopped onion in small amount of oleo, then brown hamburger with onion.
Add tomato soup plus 4 cans of water.
Add red beans, salt and pepper and chili powder to taste.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with croissants or bagel.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add flour; mix well.
Pour in milk all at once; stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Mix until blended.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, crackers, garlic powder, onion, and egg.
Shape into balls.
Place in skillet with water and brown, turning occasionally.
Drain.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer slowly.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Stir thoroughly. Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Boil noodles until almost tender, drain and rinse.
Pour 1/3 meat sauce into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with noodles, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese. Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: sausage minestrone
directions: Brown sausage with onion and garlic. Drain fat. Add remaining ingredients except beans, spaghetti and cheese. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Simmer for 1 hour. Stir in beans and spaghetti. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Simmer 10 minutes. Serve, topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Mix flour and sugar. Add milk and eggs and beat well. Stir in vinegar and vanilla.
Add butter and nuts and pour into crusts.
Place in cold oven and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: yogurt salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
Flavor may be varied by adding a bit of chives, watercress or parsley.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: gran's mac-n-cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package; drain.
Mix together 2 beaten eggs, small can of pet milk and small carton of whipping cream.
Add to macaroni.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with lots of cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees until firm.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Combine all ingredient in mixing bowl and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan that's been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: festive crescents
directions: Combine spinach, Velveeta cubes, bread crumbs and bacon in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until cheese melts.
Unroll dough; separate into 16 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise, forming 32 triangles.
Spread each triangle with 1 teaspoon of mixture.
Roll up, starting at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Makes 32.

title: stuffed date cookies
directions: Stuff dates with pecan halves.
Cream sugar with shortening. Beat in egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture.
Stir in stuffed dates.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool. Top with frosting.
Yields about 70 cookies.

title: white bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, and sugar.
Pour over beans and onions. Chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil 4 large, unpeeled sweet potatoes or enough to make 3 cups when mashed. Peel and place in mixing bowl. Mash well with a fork. With a wooden spoon, stir in the sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla, nutmeg, raisins and sour cream. Mix well. Add salt and baking soda and stir. Spread the mixture in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. When done, place marshmallows and pecans, if desired, on top and put casserole back in oven until marshmallows melt and lightly brown.

title: sesame noodles
directions: Place sesame seed in hot, dry skillet and toss gently over high heat until lightly toasted.
Set aside.
Cut scallions into 2 1/2-inch pieces.
Make fringe on one end.
Drop into ice water so they turn into brushes; set aside.

title: pecan coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Spread pecans in bottom of pan.
Pile in frozen rolls.
Sprinkle rolls with pudding.
Melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour mixture over rolls.
Set in cold oven overnight.
When raised (next morning), bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cooked cake icing
directions: Put 1/2 of milk in double boiler; heat and use other half with flour to make a paste.
Put paste into heated milk and cook until very thick and heavy, almost like a ball, stirring constantly.
Let cool until thoroughly cold.
Put in mixer and add the remaining ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.

title: cherry blossom wreaths
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Use spoon handle to make a hole in center of each to form a wreath.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet approximately 8 minutes.
Immediately remove to wire racks to cool.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Fold together dry ingredients, apples and nuts.
Fold together egg mixture and dry ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and smooth top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream for a special treat.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in dry ingredients, carrots and raisins.
Mix well.
Spray muffin tin (12-cup) with Pam.
Divide mixture evenly in cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili-baked franks and beans in box oven or dutch oven
directions: You will need a shallow baking dish for box oven.

title: dairy potato bake
directions: In large bowl mix potatoes, butter (1/2 cup), salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with crushed cornflakes.
Drizzle 1/4 cup melted butter and sprinkle with paprika for color.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine Milky Way bars, nuts and oleo.
Melt over low heat. Let cool.
Combine other ingredients and fold in candy mixture. Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 325° or until cake springs back.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and Accent.
Mix well.
Chip ham fine or use a food processor.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: brown sugar muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Blend in the brown sugar.
Combine the egg, oil and milk.
Stir into the dry ingredients until just moistened.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until done.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: work person's roast
directions: Place roast in center of a large sheet of foil.
Cut slits in roast and push in cut sections of garlic.
Pour mushroom soup over roast; pour Worcestershire over soup.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over that.
Add seasoned salt (1/4 teaspoon), salt (1/4 teaspoon) and pepper to taste.
Pull foil up and seal tight.
Leave space above and around roast.
Place in pan to cook in oven from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m. at 250°.
This makes its own gravy.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: In a large bowl combine the mix, butter or margarine, eggs and water.
Mix well.
The batter will be stiff.
Stir in pieces. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cranberry sauce salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Whip the wire whisk.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Drop by spoon on Pam-sprayed cookie sheet in small balls. Press with wet hand and bake at 350° for about ten minutes or until brown.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Brown meat in small amount of vegetable oil.
Add soup and water.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients; cook for 30 more minutes.
More water may be added if necessary.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Roll graham crackers fine.
Mix coconut, pecans, raisins, cherries and graham crackers all in a large container.
Chop and mix fine.
Heat oleo (spray coat with Pam).
Add marshmallows, 1 lb at a time.
Add milk last.
Mix well and add to other.
Pack in real fine containers.
Great at Christmastime.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Pour oil into an 8-inch round baking dish.
Add 1/3 zucchini, Mozzarella, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese, salt and parsley. Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Pour in water and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° about 45 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: beth's no bake cookies
directions: Mix
sugar and cocoa. Add milk and margarine. Bring to a slow boil (about 1 1/2 minutes).
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix until peanut butter dissolves. Add oats. Makes two 8 x 8-inch pans and 1 small round pan.

title: chile
directions: Saute beef in large pot until brown; drain fat.
Chop up onions and pepper; add to meat.
Cook until onions look clear. Add everything else.
Cook on low for a while.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat together the sugar, Crisco, butter and eggs.
Add sour cream.
Mix baking powder to 3 cups flour. Add flour mixture to 1/2 cup milk. Add flavorings. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes, celery, peppers and onions until done and put through sieve.
Mix together butter, flour, sugar and salt; add to tomato mixture and boil for 20 minutes.
Pack into jars.
Very good.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook, peel and mash sweet potatoes. Combine in a large mixing bowl with butter, eggs, milk, vanilla and sugar.
Spread in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Mix well.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Add unbaked top crust. Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: spinach madeleine
directions: Marinate snake meat in beach water for half a century.
Peel and cut ambition. Dice organization into cubes. Slice affection generously and spread evenly over laughter.
Trim sunshine precisely and pour over ingredients.
Combine above mixture in a large container. Add a pinch of wit and a dash of humor. Sprinkle with
a bit of political flavor.
Simmer in the educational system for 30 years.
Serve with an abundance of kindness (buffet style).

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and flour until like cornmeal.
Put in unbaked, 9-inch pie crust.
Pour cream over mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save 1/2 quart of chicken broth. When chicken is cool enough to handle, remove skin and bones. Cook noodles in 1/2 quart of chicken broth.
Cook onions and bell peppers in butter.
When noodles are done, add onions, peppers and Ro-Tel.
Cook over heat for 5 minutes.
Take off of stove.
Add mushroom soup and cheese until melted.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 325° until cheese is bubbly.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips together.
Pour cereal in a paper grocery sack, then pour melted mixture onto cereal.
Shake bag until cereal is covered with chocolate mixture, then pour powdered sugar over cereal and shake again until cereal is covered.

title: diabetic peach cobbler
directions: Spray a 10 x 10-inch pan with Pam.
Melt margarine.
Mix together flour, milk, vanilla and half of the melted margarine in pan.
Then pour in flour mixture.
Spread evenly.
Mix peaches and sweetener; pour over batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serving size is 3/4 cup.

title: texas torte no. 2(breakfast casserole)
directions: Blend eggs, flour, salt and pepper well and add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: hummus
directions: In food processor, add drained garbanzo beans, tahini, lemon juice, garlic cloves and salt.
Beat all ingredients together in food processor until smooth.
Add a little of drained water at a time so consistency of finished product is like sour cream. Spread in a flat plate.
Sprinkle with olive oil and a dash of paprika.
Eat with pita bread.

title: crock-pot barbecued roast
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper; place in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Turn to low and cook for 10 hours longer. Remove roast; trim off fat and remove bone.
Pour juice from crock-pot.
Put roast back in pot, pour barbecue sauce over roast and cook on low 8 to 10 hours longer.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns, if desired.
Roast may be started around six in the evening and be ready for the next day's evening meal.

title: ginger balls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well-beaten egg and molasses. Mix soda and spices with sifted flour.
Combine with first mixture. Roll into 1-inch balls, then in sugar.
Place far apart on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: outside grilled asparagus rolls
directions: Cut edge off bread.
Flatten out with rolling pin.
Spread cream cheese on flattened bread and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Melt butter in dish.
Take an asparagus spear, starting on a corner of the bread, roll the spear tip in the bread, then dip in the melted butter.
After all spears have been wrapped and dipped, put them on your hot grill until toasted, turning as needed.
The taste will surprise you!
(Start cooking about 10 minutes before your meat is done.)

title: orange cashew rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add water, orange juice and rind and salt.
Bring mixture to a boil and add rice.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in cashews and orange segments.
If fresh fruit is preferred, pineapple or nectarines are very good.
Serves 6.

title: cornbread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into an iron skillet (grease bottom of skillet).
Bake at 375° until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach crumbly crust
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Put in pan.
Mix flour, margarine and sugar until crumbly.
Spread over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Cut up tomatoes, onions and pepper.
Leave tomatoes and onions in large pieces.
Mix all well and boil 1 minute.
Put in jars and seal.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix in bowl.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.

title: festive holiday punch
directions: Pour juices into a punch bowl. Fifteen minutes before serving, add carbonated beverages. Do not stir. Serves 28.

title: pumpkin cheese bread
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese and margarine, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cool about 5 minutes and remove from pans.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Beat butter and
sugar	very well.
Add egg; beat well. Stir in vanilla	and flour.
If too soft, refrigerate until it hardens slightly.
Roll
1	tablespoon of dough in sesame seed (roasted). Flatten slightly.
Bake
for 15 to 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: pecan sour cream waffles
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar together.
Add sour cream. Separate eggs, beat yolks and add to mixture, mixing thoroughly. Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Add chopped pecan meats.
Bake in a hot waffle iron.
Makes 6 waffle.

title: chewy pecan pie squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Press in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake oatmeal and coconut cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Add margarine and milk. Put on heat and stir until it comes to a rolling boil.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper to cool or in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple mysterious dessert(not a pie - not a cake - not a pudding)
directions: Sift together first six ingredients.
Stir in unbeaten eggs and vanilla.
Fold in apple and walnuts.
Turn into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown. Garnish with whipped cream, sprinkled with cinnamon.

title: cheesy vegetable bake(microwave)
directions: Combine frozen vegetables and celery in a 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 12 to 13 minutes or until vegetables are just about thawed, stirring once. Drain by lifting the plastic wrap from one corner
and holding the dish and vegetables in place with a towel-covered hand. Remove plastic wrap.

title: texas sunday ranch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let set for a few minutes.
Use partly baked pie shells (deep dish).
Pour some mix in shell.
Let stand a few minutes.
Pour in more.
Bake in a 365° oven about 50 minutes.

title: grandma's syrup pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add to eggs.
Add butter and syrup.
Add pecans last.
Bake in an uncooked pie shell in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
This is for an 8-inch pie plate.

title: indonesian chicken
directions: Mix honey, soy sauce and ginger (can do all in food processor).
Arrange chicken in large shallow pan and pour on the sauce (it should cover by 1/4-inch).
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake 3 hours at 325°
or 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Uncover for last half hour or so.
The longer it bakes the better.
Serves 8.

title: taco pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with an electric mixer. Spread in pie dish or casserole dish.
Leave uncovered and refrigerate overnight.

title: brownie drops
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Stir; cool.
Beat eggs until foamy, then add sugar slowly.
Blend in chocolate.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cookies feel "set" when lightly touched (8 to 10 minutes).

title: blender custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle nutmeg and coconut on top.
Grease 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk slowly until it will form a soft ball in cold water.
Take it from heat and add marshmallows and peanut butter.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Pour into a buttered, flat dish to cool.
When cool, cut into squares and serve.

title: chicken teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Marinate chicken for 1 hour in refrigerator, turning at 30 minutes.
Best when charcoal grilled. Serve with rice.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper, beans and 2/3 cup onions in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes. Serves 6.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: lemon raspberry ribbon pie
directions: In a small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until thickened and clear.
Cool 10 minutes.
Chill thoroughly, about 20 minutes.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Heat milk, but do not boil.
Add marshmallows; cool.
Add all ingredients, except half of cracker crumbs.
After mixing well, add as much more crumbs as will work in.
Roll cake in leftover crumbs.
May use all crumbs or may not; varies.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough onto pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cookie. Arrange fruit.
Mix marmalade with a little hot water.
Drizzle over pizza.
Chill and cut into wedges.
Serve.

title: good cool punch
directions: Cut pieces of apple.
Then put banana in it.
Freeze it.
Then you put water on it.
Then you let it dry for 5 hours.
Then after that, you put slices of onion in it.
Then put more water in it.
Then put it on the stove to let it get hot.
Then you wait for a few seconds for it to get ready.
Then you eat it.
(If you don't like the onion, you can take them out.)

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix well first three ingredients.
Beat in egg; add soda and water and vanilla.

title: haystacks
directions: Simmer beans to blend flavors.
Purchase corn chips or brush uncooked tortillas with water and sprinkle with onion salt or garlic salt.
Lay on cookie sheet and dry out in 200° oven.
Break into little pieces.

title: jerome bars
directions: Line 9 x 15-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Set aside. Melt oleo.
Add sugar.
Beat egg into milk.
Add to butter and sugar mixture.
Boil, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut, pecans and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Spread mixture over whole crackers.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers.

title: upside down cobbler
directions: Combine and mix well the flour, sugar, margarine and egg. Add and mix well milk, baking powder and pinch of salt.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at approximately 350° until done.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Cook and cut up chicken.
Butter 9 x 13 dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Use 1/2 bag of Ritz or 1 large sleeve crushed and pour over chicken mixture.
Melt oleo with poppy seeds and pour over crackers.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: new fashioned bread pudding with strawberry sauce
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 12 x 8-inch baking dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Cut bread into chunks.
In large bowl, with wire whisk or fork, beat milk, brown sugar, vanilla and egg substitute until well blended.
Add bread chunks and raisins; toss to coat.
Let bread soak in milk mixture for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cold spinach soup
directions: In large frying pan, melt butter and saute scallions. Transfer to large bowl and add spinach, potato soup, chicken broth, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Puree in blender or food processor.
Put back into bowl and stir in cream and sour cream. Chill at least 8 hours.
Garnish with chopped parsley and/or lemon rind.
Serves 8.

title: catfish chowder
directions: Boil catfish until tender (can remove bones) with onion and potato (until tender).
Add
milk,	cornstarch
and margarine.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and chop potatoes, cover with water.
Boil until tender, do not drain.
Add margarine, sour cream, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and mash until very small lumps remain.
Add enough instant potatoes to mixture to absorb excess soup.
Whip with spoon until light and fluffy.
Serve hot.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Smash garlic and put all the ingredients into a pot.
Cover and bring to a rapid boil.
Reduce to medium heat and simmer until meat is done.
Serve with rice.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Cut up rhubarb; mix well with sugar and pineapple.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
In the morning, boil for 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add the gelatin.
Return to stove; boil for 1 minute longer, then pour into jars.
Let cool, seal and store.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Boil rhubarb until tender.
Add sugar and Jell-O.
Stir well. Put in jars and refrigerate or freeze.

title: creole franks and rice
directions: Saut green pepper, celery and onion in margarine. Add rice, tomatoes and salt. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add the franks and simmer for 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix and marinate overnight. Top with bacon crumbs.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pour peaches into a 9 x 13 pan. Over peaches, pour dry cake mix. Pat butter on top of mixture, then sprinkle over top the cinnamon and sugar. Bake until brown on top, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese and vegetable casserole
directions: Heat milk; pour over bread crumbs.
Add pimento, parsley, onion, grated cheese and seasonings.
Then add eggs.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes (either hot or cold) with oil, vinegar, pickle liquid, dill, onion and garlic.
Set aside to marinate for several hours in the refrigerator.
Chop green onions fine; slice radishes thin.
Quarter hard-cooked eggs.
Add to potatoes with remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Serves 6.

title: gumbo
directions: Cook celery, onion and flour in oil for 5 minutes; stir as needed.
Add remaining ingredients, except chicken, shrimp and rice.
Stir well.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add chicken and shrimp.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: knippy clams
directions: Melt shortening and mix with flour and juice.
Cook and stir until smooth, then put in slightly beaten egg yolk for 2 minutes and cook slowly.
Add seasoning and clams.
Pour into baking dish. Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: country ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with assorted crackers or on cocktail biscuits.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well. Cover and chill. Garnish with pepper rings.

title: baked broccoli and beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in ungreased 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake for 1 hour, or until rice and broccoli are tender.

title: peaches for fried pies(this peach filling can be frozen or canned)
directions: Mix and cook ingredients until thick or until consistency of peach preserves (it should not be too runny or juicy).
Put in hot, pint jars while boiling hot and seal; or you can put in freezer containers and freeze.

title: the very best brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening over low heat.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy; add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in alternately with chocolate mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In large bowl of mixer pour cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, oil and eggs.
Mix for 10 minutes on high speed.
In a separate bowl combine sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Spray a Bundt pan with non-stick spray.
Sprinkle in 1/3 of the cinnamon mixture, top with 1/2 the cake mixture, another 1/3 cinnamon mixture, the rest of cake mixture, then the remaining 1/3 cinnamon mixture.
Take a knife and swirl through the batter layers.
Bake at 350°
for 55-60 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool 3-4 minutes before inverting onto a plate

title: mulled wine
directions: Place sugar, water, orange slices, cloves and cinnamon in a large saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the juice and wine.
Keep hot but do not boil.
Serve with cinnamon sticks or orange slices.

title: yummy fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and arrange on a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Flour fingers and press dough all over pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Combine egg and next 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add onion and meat and mix well.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix each pack of jello with 1 1/2 cup of hot water, dissolve. Pour into flat dish (not too deep).
Let congeal; cut into 1 inch cubes.
Add the jello cubes to the whipped Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows, crushed pineapple and pecans; mix together.
Let set until firm.

title: red hot applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 6 cups boiling water.
Dissolve candy in 2 cups boiling water.
Combine jello and red hot solution.
Add applesauce and mix well. Pour into a 15 x 18 x 2-inch pan.
Let stand overnight. Cut into 7 x 5-inch pieces.
Serves 35.

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix together tomatoes and onions and put into pie crust. Sprinkle with Pepper Seasoning Mix. Mix together mayonnaise and cheese and spread on top of dressing mix. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients and spread on cookie crust.
Drain pineapple well. Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange slices touching on 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until brown.
Let cool.
Spread on cream cheese mixture, then crushed pineapple.
Arrange banana slices on pineapple and next sliced strawberries.
Sprinkle with flaked coconut.
If desired, sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts and chocolate chips.

title: garbage dip
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve with veggies, crackers, bread sticks or chips.

title: buckwheat pancakes with maple-nut syrup
directions: Combine flours, rolled oats, baking powder, baking soda, orange zest and salt in a mixing bowl.
In another bowl, whisk together buttermilk, eggs and melted butter.
Add buttermilk mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Do not overmix; the batter will have small lumps.
Let batter rest at room temperature 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Sprinkle some of the cinnamon sugar onto greased and floured pan (Bundt pan or regular cake pan).
Pour in half of the batter.
Pour most of the cinnamon sugar onto the batter.
Pour in remainder of batter; sprinkle with remainder of cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sugar coated nuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water over medium heat.
Add peanuts and cook on medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cook until peanuts are completely coated.
Pour and spread on ungreased cookie sheet. Cook for 30 minutes in 330° oven.
Shake a few times while in oven.
Let cool and store in airtight container.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Peel and slice carrots into 1-inch chunks.
Coarsely chop red onion.
Steam carrots and Brussels sprouts for 5 minutes.
Add onion.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Drain and add butter and salt to taste.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until pie is solid.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight before serving.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and sugar; mix with corn meal. Combine eggs, milk and shortening; add to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Bake in waxed paper lined 9-inch square pan or a black cast-iron skillet preheated with hot oil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 16 squares.

title: creamy cheese cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: simple roast turkey
directions: Will also need 1 turkey size oven bag.
Preparation Time: 10 minutes.
Cooking Time:
2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar and
vinegar	with salad dressing.
Pour over broccoli, raisins, onion
and
crumbled
bacon bits.
Mix well and refrigerate a couple of hours to blend flavors.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut a slice in stem end of peppers.
Remove seeds and thoroughly wash.
Bring 3/4 cup salted water per pepper to boil, add peppers and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove peppers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook beef, garlic and onion in skillet until onion is tender.
Drain off fat and stir in salt, rice and half the tomato sauce.
Heat mixture; remove from heat, add Cheddar cheese.
Stuff each pepper and stand upright in baking dish.
Pour rest of tomato sauce over peppers and bake, covered 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: mother's orange candy slice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, salt, soda and buttermilk. Mix thoroughly.
Add 2 cups flour and nuts.
Mix remaining 1 cup flour with candy slices and dates.
Cut candy and dates into small pieces, add to cake mixture.
Add coconut, mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: hershey's chocolate syrup cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix flour and baking powder separate.
Mix flour in sugar mixture slowly.
Then add can of Hershey's chocolate syrup and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and bake at 350° for 40 minutes until done.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, then chips and pecans; makes a stiff dough.
Drop by tablespoon or shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° just until edges brown.
When slightly cool, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 90 cookies.

title: crunchy dessert
directions: Spread graham cracker crumbs on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle evenly chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Pour condensed milk all over.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Cook pudding according to directions and set aside to cool. Line 2-quart dish with vanilla wafers, then alternate layers of pudding, berries and wafers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Frozen berries work best.

title: grandma's pear cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or more.

title: raisin-filled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 1/8 teaspoon salt in a saucepan.
Blend in water and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add raisins. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream shortening and brown sugar in mixer bowl.
Blend in eggs.
Add 3 1/2 cups flour, 1 tablespoon vanilla, 1/8 teaspoon salt and soda; mix well.
Chill dough.

title: chicken enchilada ring
directions: Chop chicken and olives. Add cheese, chilies and mayonnaise. Seed & chop tomato. Slice lime in 1/2.
Squeeze the 1/2
to measure 1 tsp.
juice. Keep other half for garnish. Add chopped tomato & lime juice to chicken mixture. Reserve

2 Tbsp crushed chips. Add remaining chips to chicken mixture & mix well. Sprinkle crushed chips over cookie sheet. Unroll crescent rolls. Place sticky side down on chips. Separate into triangles. Arrange triangles chip side down. Place
scope of chicken mixture on rolls. Bring points of triangles up over filling. Bake 20-25 minutes. Garnish with lime slices. Serve with sour cream, salsa, & chopped tomato.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Put soda in milk.
Put salt and baking powder in flour.
Add both to butter mixture.
Add crushed bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 375° until tests done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the potatoes, brown sugar, oleo, milk and eggs; put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: monkey faced cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375° (quick moderate).
Mix shortening, sugar and molasses thoroughly.
Mix milk and vinegar; stir in.
Measure flour by dipping method (or by sifting).
Stir dry ingredients together; blend into sugar mixture.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Place 3 jelly beans on each for eyes and mouth.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Allow to remain on baking sheet 1 minute before removing. The faces take on droll expressions in baking.
Makes about 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: peach bread
directions: Puree peaches and 6 tablespoons of sugar in blender.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and margarine until fluffy. Add eggs, beating well.

title: lynette's salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain blueberries, pineapple and to their juice add enough water to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add to jello mixture.
Refrigerate.
When slightly thickened, add pineapple and blueberries.
Refrigerate.
When firm, frost with topping of cheese, sour cream, vanilla and sugar which has been beaten together.
Sprinkle the nuts on top.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Pour in frozen pie crust and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot balls
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shape into balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Roll in eggs and crumbs and fry in deep hot fat (375° to 385°) until browned. Drain on absorbent paper.

title: barbecued franks
directions: In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Place in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans with frankfurters in single layer.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until frankfurters are hot and glazed.
Serve warm with toothpicks.
Makes 24 servings.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: Mix well, then stir in 1 small box lemon instant pudding. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Cream the cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Fill the celery with the mixture.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: boneless chicken breasts
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter, then in remaining ingredients. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and dice all fruit.
Mix together all ingredients, except bananas, since they will turn dark in a few hours.
Just before serving, add bananas.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in bowl.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cornflakes and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and shred.
Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix soup and mayo together.
Place broccoli in greased 13X9 pan, then chicken, then soup mix.
Cover with Cheddar.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix ingredients together. Put in pot and let come to boil. Add squash; simmer 3 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and hot mustard
directions: Mix together mustard and cider vinegar.
Let stand overnight. Slightly beat eggs and sugar.
Mix together and add to mustard mixture.
Cool until thick.
Makes 1 pint.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Chop green onions fine.
Chop green pepper.
Add all ingredients except pecans.
Mix thoroughly; shape into ball and chill for several hours.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Soften margarine in bowl.
Add next four ingredients.
Do not stir.
Cook on Full power for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and pecans. Beat with mixer until well blended.
Pour into greased dish. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain off fat from ground round.
Mix together with Cheddar cheese, Doritos, lettuce, tomatoes, green peppers and onion.
Mix together Western dressing and taco sauce; pour over salad.

title: wine cookies
directions: Beat eggs very well until light.
Add sugar, oil, wine and flavoring. Begin with 5 cups of flour. Add small amounts at a time to make a soft dough, not sticky.
Roll into ropes and make into desired shapes of twists and/or circles.
Dab white wine on tops of cookie, then dip into white sugar before placing on cookie sheet.
I do not grease my cookie sheet. Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 - 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Combine apple juice concentrate, cornstarch and spices in a saucepan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt, apples and artificial sweetener.
Pour into one of the pie shells.
Top with remaining pie shells, sealing edges and cutting vents.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 400° until golden brown. Yield:
8 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and syrup.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together, then add hot water last and beat until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inch) for 35 minutes at 350° or when you insert toothpick in center and it comes out clean.
Cool in pan and cover with any simple icing.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and Miracle Whip together. Grate and mix Swiss and Mozzarella together.
Layer all ingredients in order in a large salad bowl. This should be made 24 hours in advance so flavors will mix. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Do not shake or toss. When serving, dip straight down through all layers to the bottom.

title: chicken casserole #2
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in buttered casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs, crackers or bread.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.
Use a 10 x 6-inch baking casserole dish. (It is just as good without the chestnuts.)

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste.
Cook 40 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: turkey stew
directions: Cook turkey on stove until done.
Remove skin and bones and cut in small pieces.
Put potatoes, onions, fatback and turkey broth on washpot outside; add water.
Cook until potatoes and onions are tender.
Add cut-up turkey and tomato juice.
Cook until slightly thick.
Add corn, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, butter and tomato paste.
Put in seasonings.
Stir constantly.
Add pepper and Texas Pete to taste.
Makes about 20 quarts.
Takes about 1 1/2 hours to finish.

title: broiled squirrel
directions: Salt and pepper the squirrels.
Brush with lard and broil on a rack about 40 minutes.
Baste with drippings every 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grilled minted leg of lamb
directions: Combine marinade ingredients in a large shallow glass or ceramic container. Add lamb. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate at least 4 hours.
Turn during marinating.

title: butterscotch spiders
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in double boiler.
Mix in can of Chinese noodles and peanuts.
Stir until all is coated.
Spoon out onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Store in a sealed container to retain freshness.

title: zesty lasagna
directions: Microwave Directions:
Crumble beef into a 2-quart casserole. Add garlic.
Cover with wax paper; microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes, or until meat is done, stirring twice.
Drain.
Stir in tomato paste, water, mushrooms, bay leaves, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and oregano.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High for 4 to 5 minutes, or until mixture is thoroughly heated, stirring once.
Remove bay leaves; set aside.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine beaten egg, milk, chopped apples, sugar, salt, orange peel, orange juice and vanilla. Stir together flour and baking powder. Fold into egg mixture, stirring just until all flour is moistened. Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls in oil, heated to 350°. Fry until deep golden brown, about 3 to 4 minutes, turning once. Drain on paper towel. Roll in sugar. Makes 40 fritters.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix together flour, oleo and nuts with a pastry cutter.
Press mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; gradually beat in well-beaten eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly until slightly thickened (about 5 minutes). Beat in salad dressing.
Combine all other ingredients in separate bowl. Pour dressing over potato mixture.
Toss gently.
Serves 6.

title: mango fruit parfait
directions: In blender, puree mangoes and orange juice until smooth. Slice 20 strawberries (leave 4 whole for garnish).
Line bottom of balloon wine glasses with sliced strawberries.
Pour a thin layer of mango over each to cover.
Reserve 4 kiwi slices; layer rest on top of puree.
Divide remainder of puree among glasses.
Top with a slice of kiwi and surround with raspberries.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 15 minutes.

title: japanese mandarin ham rolls
directions: Drain juice from orange segments. Combine juice, bread crumbs, chives and sage.
Roll each ham slice around about 1 tablespoon of stuffing.
Place rolls in shallow baking dish.
Combine marmalade, vinegar, mustard and mandarin segments.
Pour over ham rolls. Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 servings of 2 rolls each.

title: quick potato kugel *
directions: Grind potatoes with onion and carrots in blender or processor. Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake one hour or until browned in preheated 375° oven. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweetened condensed milk(yields one can)
directions: Blend in blender, water, sugar and nonfat dry milk powder. Refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use potato chips or crackers for dipping.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside. In another large bowl, stir Raisin Bran and milk to combine.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to cereal mixture and stir until mixed only.
Pour batter evenly into 12 greased muffin cups.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and stem mushrooms.
Fry sausage; drain well.
Add cream cheese and garlic; mix.
Fill mushrooms with mixture.
Place in pan with 1/4 cup butter, melted.
Sprinkle Parmesan over mushrooms. Dot with remaining butter.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: asparagus almondine
directions: Layer asparagus, eggs and cheese in buttered casserole dish. Combine soup and milk and pour over. Top with almonds and bread crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy microwave chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg; roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place in Pyrex casserole dish and drizzle with butter.
Cover with wax paper and cook on High for 15 to 20 minutes. Turn once.

title: unbelievable lasagne
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce. Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagne.
Top with some sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce.
Repeat, gently pressing lasagne pieces into cheese mixture.
End with a final layer of lasagne; pour remaining sauce over, making sure all lasagne pieces are covered with sauce.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan (do not be concerned with the empty space at the ends of the pan; during cooking, the lasagne will expand and take up most of the area).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until lightly browned and bubbling.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: florentine dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine first 8 ingredients, blending until smooth.
Stir in 1/4 cup Cheddar and 1/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese.
Spread mixture into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange chopped artichoke hearts around edge of plate.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses on top and bake 5 minutes longer or until bubbly.
Serve warm with tortilla wedges.

title: different salad
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper, fresh tomatoes and Velveeta cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle sugar over all.
Add Miracle Whip.
This is delicious with Mexican food, fish or any meat.

title: fantasy fudge(doubled)
directions: Stir together sugar, oleo and milk in heavy 5 quart pan. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.
Yields 6 pounds.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Slowly add 4 cups sugar to the milk, blending well.
Mix in the salt and extracts.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup sugar on a board; knead the fondant until smooth and creamy, working in the sugar.
Wrap in foil; let set in refrigerator for a day.
Stuff the dates and top them with walnut halves, if desired.

title: washboard cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and egg.
Stir together baking soda and water.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet; flatten with forks dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese strata
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Butter bread and quarter each slice. Alternate layers of bread and cheese in baking dish, ending with cheese on top.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over layers. Cover and chill 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken and stuffing rouladen
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir margarine into hot chicken broth in bowl until melted.
Add stuffing crumbs, red pepper and beaten egg white.
Stir until moist.
Spoon chicken stuffing over chicken. Evenly roll.
Tightly secure with toothpick.
Place in greased square baking dish.
Brush with butter and pepper.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Heat soup, water, wine and dill.
Serve over chicken.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain juices from the vegetables and reserve 1 tablespoon bean juice.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Cream oil, sugar and egg.
Add sour or buttermilk.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix all together.
Bake.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cook at 350° until pie sets (about 35 minutes).

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine egg yolk, brown sugar, milk, salt and spices. Cook in double boiler until thick. Soften gelatin in cool water. Add to hot mixture. When cool, beat egg whites stiff. Add 1/2 cup sugar. Add to pumpkin mixture. Pour in two 9-inch pie shells. Top with whipped cream. Enjoy.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, white sugar, milk, eggs, 1/2 stick margarine and drained pineapple.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.

title: candied yams(will serve 15 to 20 people)
directions: Note:
Need 1 large Dutch oven or boiler and 1 medium mixing bowl.

title: italian vegetable crouton bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In each of three small mixing bowls, toss sliced squash with garlic salt; stir Italian Blend into tomatoes and toss onion with Italian pepper.
Set these bowls aside.
Spray 3 or 4-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer 1 cup croutons, 1 cup squash mixture, 1 cup tomato mixture, 1/2 cup onion mixture and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Repeat this process.
Pour melted margarine evenly over top.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring 2 quarts water to a boil.
Add noodles.
Return to a boil; add 1 pound broccoli pieces and return to a boil.
In a separate pan, saute carrot, onion and chicken broth until tender. Add soup; return to a boil.
Add Cheddar cheese soup and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add milk that has been heated.
Ready to serve.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown onion and sausage in 4-quart saucepan; drain fat.
Add water, basil, whole tomatoes (break up) and broth.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add zucchini and garbanzos.
Serve when zucchini becomes tender. Sprinkle soup with Parmesan if desired.

title: crispy cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies may have to be mixed with your hands; very stiff dough.
Roll into small balls; mash down with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate chip melt aways
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat until smooth.
Combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add butter mixture.
Beat until smooth; stir in vanilla and chocolate chips.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned (do not overbake).
Makes 9 dozen.

title: creamy holiday fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Set aside. Combine egg yolks, sugar and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Gradually add reserved pineapple juice, vinegar and butter.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cool.
Combine pineapple, cherries and miniature marshmallows in a bowl.
Fold egg mixture into whipped cream. Pour over fruit, stirring gently to coat.
Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: hoppin john(south carolina)
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon slices until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels, reserving 2 tablespoons dripping in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add onion, green pepper, celery and garlic to reserved drippings.
Cook until nearly tender.
Stir in black-eyed peas, beef broth, thyme, marjoram and red pepper.
Stir in cooked rice; heat through.
Garnish with bacon, tomato and green onion.

title: napa valley chicken bake
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
In a small bowl, combine the flour, oregano, garlic, paprika, salt and pepper.
Dust the chicken with all the mixture (this will help thicken the sauce).
In a large skillet, heat the oil. Brown the chicken. Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with the onions and mushrooms.
In a separate bowl, mix together the sour cream, tomato paste and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over the chicken. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove cover the last 5 minutes of cooking time. Good served with fluffy rice, marinated asparagus and poached pears with lingonberry sauce for dessert.

title: beef stroganoff and noodles
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips. In skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef until browned, stirring often. Set aside. Add soup, water, onion and broth. Heat to boiling. Stir in noodles. Cook over low heat until noodles are done, stirring often. Stir in yogurt. Return beef to pan and heat thoroughly.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Layer chicken, soup mixture and crackers. Repeat.
Pour melted butter all over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: With meat at room temperature, mix all ingredients by hand very well.
Pinch off into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes on middle rack.
Cool.
Store in plastic bag, 25 to a bag, and freeze.
When ready to serve, heat in an oven at 300° for 10 minutes.
Do not thaw before heating!
Makes about 125 sausage balls.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season wings with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place in a shallow baking dish and bake for 15 minutes.
In a small saucepan, combine ketchup, vinegar, sugar and water.
heat, stirring, until well blended.
Brush sauce over wings and continue to bake for 20 to 30 minutes, or until wings are tender.
Remove from oven and serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook, drain and spread sausage in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle cubed bread over sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over bread and sausage; top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: orange delight
directions: Sprinkle unmade Jell-O over cottage cheese. Add oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip
and pour into mold. Chill 2 hours.

title: uncooked ozark relish
directions: Tie the spices in a bag and place in the pan with the other ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes and then add the rind.
Boil for 30 minutes or longer, if you want the melon more like preserves. Remove the spice bag.
Put the melon pieces in sterilized jars and cover with the boiling vinegar mixture.
Seal.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients but Cool Whip. Set in refrigerator overnight.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Put 5 cups diced rhubarb in greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Pour 1 cup sugar over rhubarb.
Cover with 1 box dry strawberry cake mix, dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Chop or break up lettuce.
Layer vegetables and eggs in a large flat Pyrex plate or glass bowl.
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spread, covering all vegetables.
Just before serving, add bacon and toss.

title: mexican chili casserole
directions: Reserve 1 cup corn chips and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Combine remaining chips and cheese with chili, sauces and onion.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes (until heated).
Spread top with sour cream; sprinkle remaining chips and cheese on top.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: velveeta dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Melt cheese and soup and add salsa.
Mix well and add to sausage.
Serve warm with favorite chips.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Blend together margarine, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Add next 4 ingredients, alternating with the sour cream.
Add vanilla last. Blend crushed walnuts (optional), cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour half of batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan, then sprinkle half of the cinnamon, sugar and walnut mixture over batter.
Add remaining batter to pan; sprinkle remaining cinnamon, sugar and walnut mixture on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients except butter and garlic powder.
Mix with wooden spoon until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by heaping tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in preheated 450° oven.
Combine butter and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: country beans
directions: Brown meats in skillet; drain.
Stir in tomatoes and gravy mix in casserole.
Add beans and molasses and onions.
Pierce sausage links with cloves.
Arrange on top of casserole and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with butter and arrange in alternate layers as follows:
Asparagus, soup, bread crumbs and egg slices. Pour over this sweet milk and dot top with butter.
Bake in moderate-hot oven about 40 minutes.

title: barbecues
directions: Add all ingredients to the fried ground beef and onion.

title: french toast
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cover with 2 layers of 6 slices of bread.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over bread.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Invert onto serving platter.
Serve with syrup or powdered sugar.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and flour; beat gently.
Add remaining ingredients and beat slightly.
Preheat oven to 400°. Reduce heat to 200° while cooking.
Cook until golden in color and firm consistency.

title: beet juice jelly to serve with meats
directions: (Juices from pickled beets can be used.)

title: tuna baked potato
directions: Bake potatoes in microwave.
Cut in half lengthwise, remove inside, leaving skin.
Mash potatoes with milk and salt.
Stir in tuna, cheese and chives.
Spoon evenly divided, back into skins and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a shallow pan at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until top is browned.

title: sugarless apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put raisins and water in saucepan. Cook, uncovered, until water is evaporated and fruit is soft.
Set aside to cool.

title: coke salad
directions: Mix warm cream cheese and dry jello in glass bowl. Drain juice from cherries and pineapple to make 1 cup.
Heat juices just to boiling; pour over mixture, stirring thoroughly. Refrigerate until thick and syrupy, not set.
Add cold Coke, stirring thoroughly.
Refrigerate to same consistency. Add hand mashed cherries, pineapple and pecans. Refrigerate until firm.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, radishes and onions.
In a separate bowl, mix together the mayonnaise, mustard powder, sugar, pepper, turmeric and celery seed.
Add vinegar and milk; stir until mixed. Combine with potato mixture; stir well.
Chill before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with paprika and more grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: carolyn's pickles
directions: Put cucumbers whole in stone pot.

title: queen's cake
directions: Mix with dates.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan, greased and floured, in 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: frosty mandarin jello dessert
directions: Drain oranges, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add measured liquid.
Add sherbert by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges, reserving a few for garnish.
Pour into a serving bowl or individual servings dishes.
Chill until set, at least one hour.
Garnish with reserved mandarin orange sections and mint leaves, if desired.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: vitamin pie
directions: Combine the sugar, flour, soda and salt. Add the egg and fruit cocktail.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Mix the brown sugar and nuts and sprinkle over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meaty manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and set aside. Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Remove from heat and add spinach, cottage cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fill each shell with 1/4 cup meat mixture.
Place filled shells in prepared baking pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce evenly over shells.
Sprinkle Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese over sauce.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter rice krispies
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter. Stir until smooth. Stir in 6 cups Rice Krispies. Spread in 9 x 13 pan.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Simmer green pepper slices in water until nearly tender. Drain.
Combine milk with mayonnaise, add pimiento, green pepper, mushrooms, water chestnuts and chicken.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix corn bread crumbs and stick of melted butter.
Mix well and use 1/2 on bottom of dish.
Save the other 1/2 for topping. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over crumbs.
Put other 1/2 of crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix soups and water.
Place meat in baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over meat.
Spread Tater Tots over meat and soup.
Bake until Tater Tots are brown on top and soft on bottom.
Bake at 350° in oven.

title: chow chow
directions: Pour salt over mixture of onions, cabbage, tomatoes and sweet peppers.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse salt brine off and drain in colander.
Next day, bring to boil sugar, celery seed, mustard seed, turmeric, vinegar and water.
Combine all ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Bring back to a boil, then simmer for 3 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes 12 pints.

title: cold crab dip
directions: Beat cheese with lemon.
Fold in crabmeat.
In separate bowl mix chili sauce with horseradish and lemon.
Layer 1/2 crabmeat with 1/2 cocktail sauce.
Repeat.
Serve with crackers.

title: harvest moon chowder
directions: Place onion, carrots, broccoli, potatoes, celery and chicken broth in large kettle or Dutch oven.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: keebler club cracker bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and put 1 layer of Club crackers. Then bring to a slow boil sugar, brown sugar, graham crackers, milk and oleo.
Pour this over the layer of crackers; then put another layer of crackers over this.
Then melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour this over the last layer of crackers.

title: rose mary's candy
directions: Blend sugar, Karo, milk and butter.
Cook over low heat until mixture forms a firm ball when dripped in cold water.
Take off heat and cool a few minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla and beat until cool.
Pour into well buttered pan.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Trim crusts from bread; cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Melt cheeses, butter or margarine in top of double boiler until of rarebit consistency.
Remove from heat; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Dip bread cubes into cheese mixture until well coated; place on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffy and golden brown. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chili
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef with chopped onions until lightly browned.
Add bean mixture; cook over medium heat approximately 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut buttered bread into cubes.
Combine ingredients in top of double boiler and cook until custard forms.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese and yogurt together; set aside.
Spread 2/3 cup spaghetti sauce in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer a third each of noodles, cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese, remaining spaghetti sauce and Parmesan.
Repeat twice.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: easy stew
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve on rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: haystacks
directions: Measure corn flakes into a large bowl and set aside. Mix sugar and corn syrup in a medium pan and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Remove from stove and add peanut butter, stirring until melted. Pour mixture over corn flakes and stir until the corn flakes are completely coated. Spoon onto wax paper forming individual "haystacks."

title: chicken salad spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on fresh bread.

title: turmeric pickles
directions: Cook all together until cucumbers look clear.
Can while hot.

title: shrimp-broccoli stir-fry
directions: Stir together broth, brown sugar and cornstarch in 1 cup glass measure.
Reserve.

title: magic cookie bar
directions: Pour melted butter or oleo into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts over crumbs.
Scatter chocolate morsels over nuts, then coconut.
Pour Eagle Brand condensed milk over.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until slightly browned on top.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 2 dozen.
No mixing.
Make right in baking pan.

title: beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle soup mix over the top of the brisket.
Wrap in heavy foil, sealing all seams so that juices do not escape.
Place in oven at 200° for
8 hours.
Slice across grain.
Make gravy from drippings.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in a little butter.
Add milk, water, potato and corn; simmer 5 minutes.
Add fish and simmer 5 more minutes till fish is flaky and potato is cooked.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large nonstick saucepan, saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add beef broth to onions with pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, covered, on low for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Put all ingredients (except vanilla) together in pot.
Cook at a rolling boil for 10 minutes at low heat.
Cool slightly and beat until light and creamy.
Add vanilla.
This will cover 6 thin layers of cake sides and top.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugars and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mix.
Add raisins, oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat together margarine, sugar, flour and milk.
Lastly add beaten eggs.
Mix only until well blended.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake just until set in middle, maybe 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Add sugar and flour to butter.
Blend well; add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour in pie shell and cook for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In a 13-inch x 9-inch x 2-inch pan sprayed with no-stick cooking spray, sprinkle the can of angel flake coconut and the pecans or walnuts.
Mix a German chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut in pan.
Cream one stick of butter, cream cheese, and box of powdered sugar together well. Drop by spoonfuls over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool, cut, and eat.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown chops and drain fat.
Return chops to skillet and top each with a slice of apple and a slice of onion. Sprinkle brown sugar over all.
Fit thick slices of sweet potatoes around pork chops.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over. Simmer until chops are tender.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Mix oil in warmed buttermilk.
(60 seconds in microwave.) Mix flour, soda, salt, sugar and yeast together.
Stir for 60 seconds.
Combine with buttermilk and oil.
Roll out in white flour and let rise until it doubles itself-about an hour at room temperature. Roll out again and cut into biscuits.
Let rise about 10 minutes.
Bake in hot oven 400°.

title: shoney's hot fudge cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and add boiling water.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lime punch
directions: Pour Sprite and ginger ale in punch bowl.
Spoon lime sherbet; stir to mix.
Add green maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: peach brandy slush
directions: Freeze all the ingredients, except 7-Up.
When ready to serve drink, mix 1/2 slush and 1/2 Seven-Up for each drink.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas. Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: partridges in brown paper
directions: Rub birds inside and out with lemon juice, sage and tarragon. Put giblets and half an onion in the cavities.
Place bacon along the breast and wrap each bird in buttered brown paper or foil.

title: classic baked ziti
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in large skillet.
Cook ziti noodles al dente and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, chicken broth and oregano to beef mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir 1 cup of sauce into drained ziti noodles.
Spoon half of noodles into 9 x 13-inch (or two 8 x 8-inch) baking dish.
Sprinkle with half Mozzarella cheese and half Parmesan cheese.
Top with half sauce. Layer rest of noodles.
Top with rest of sauce.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered for 10 minutes.
(This freezes well.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and add brown sugar; cream well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to shortening mixture.
Pour batter into a greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beet and pineapple salad
directions: Save juice of beets and pineapple.
Add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Heat.
Mix and chill.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients and set aside. In a microwave-safe bowl, heat chips and oil on medium-high for 2 minutes, stirring once.
Microwave on high for 10 seconds more; stir until smooth.
Pour over cereal mixture and mix well.
Spread evenly onto waxed paper-lined baking sheet.
Cool and break apart. Store in an airtight container.

title: transparent pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and cream.
Beat together until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Divide into the two pie shells.
Bake at 350° until set and nicely browned.

title: potato boats
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise to make boats.
Using a spoon, scrape raw potatoes to scoop out a well in potatoes, leaving about 1/4-inch thick shell.
Brown ground beef and drain off grease. Cook the potatoes you scraped out with the onion in the oil until brown.
Mix all the cooked vegetables and ground beef.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Spoon mixture into the well of the potato boat.
Pour 1/2 cup water over and around potatoes.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done. Serves 6 people.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, slightly beaten.
Add melted margarine and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake. Leave a little gooey.

title: new old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Drop large teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: quick pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in jar or large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers. Keep refrigerated. They will last several weeks.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding enough buttermilk to make a medium soft dough.
Spoon out and drop into hot grease.
Cook until brown on both sides.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Place butter, oats and water in bowl; stir well.
Cool.
Add all remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Let cake set out of oven for 5 minutes.

title: best macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
In buttered casserole dish layer macaroni, cheese and butter.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over casserole.
Cook at 375° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes.

title: homemade modeling clay(for the kids on a rainy day)
directions: Knead materials together.
Wrap in wax paper and place in coffee can.
A little water may be kneaded into the mixture if it becomes too dry.

title: easy nacho skillet dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in 10-inch skillet; drain. Stir in corn, chili powder, beans and tomato sauce. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with tortilla chips and cheese. Cover; heat about 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 6 servings.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Bake in a greased baking dish, as it browns, stir several times.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Add pineapple, pecans and cream cheese mixture to gelatin.
Chill until firm.

title: so-easy lasagna
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread about 1 cup sauce.
Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagna; top with some sauce, ground chuck, 1/2 of Ricotta, 1/2 of Mozzarella, 1/2 of Parmesan and repeat layers. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and serve with tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: beef stew with cheddar dumplings
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture. In a Dutch oven, heat oil over medium-high.
Brown meat on all sides.
Add onion salt, garlic salt, browning sauce, water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 1 hour.
Add carrots and onion.
Simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in green beans.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill dough.
Roll with hands into ball size of a walnut.
Roll ball in a mixture of two tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 400° oven.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat Butterfingers with hammer to crush.
Mix all ingredients together and put in ice cream freezer.
Fill freezer with milk. Now you can make your ice cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in a saucepan.
Drain and add enough fresh water to cover the beans.
Bring the beans to a boil, add baking soda and continue to boil until the skins split.
Drain and rinse beans.
Place beans and all other ingredients in a crock-pot.
Add enough water in the crock-pot to cover the ingredients.
Cover and cook all day adding hot water as necessary to cover ingredients.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together well and serve!!

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain. Add broth and rice in a medium-sized pot on top of stove. Cook until rice is done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of the cocoa and food coloring and add to mixture.
Slowly add vanilla, buttermilk, salt and flour.
Mix well.
