Mix together soda and vinegar and gently stir in, mixing well.
Batter will be thick.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Keep overnight.
Remove 1 hour before heating.
Sprinkle with grated American cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: sugarless spice cupcakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg and add water, sugar substitute, oil and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Divide batter equally into eight fluted paper baking cups placed in muffin tin.
Set muffin tin in a shallow pan of water and cover with an inverted cake pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove pan cover and bake 5 more minutes.
Makes eight.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Cook the ingredients until thread stage or 232°.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla extract.
Add 2 1/2 cups whole pecan halves. Pour out on tinfoil and separate with 2 forks.
Must work quickly.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar, cornstarch, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Add orange juice gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth (about 3 minutes). Pour over carrots.

title: taco casserole
directions: Put oil in skillet and saute the onion and green pepper. Add the ground meat and cook until done. Add tomatoes (with 1/4 cup juice reserved). Add the tomato sauce, Karo syrup and seasonings. Simmer 15 minutes. Blend the 1/4 cup tomato juice in the 2 tablespoons
cornstarch and
stir this into the meat mixture. Add the macaroni. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Add 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8. Can freeze.
Must do ahead.

title: chicken bola
directions: Combine flour, salt, celery salt, garlic salt and nutmeg in a paper sack.
Shake and dust the chicken.
Melt the oleo in a skillet and brown each piece of chicken.
Place in a casserole dish. Drain the pineapple. Combine 1 cup juice, soy sauce and sugar together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Put pineapple chunks on top of chicken during the last 15 minutes of baking.
Serve over rice.

title: joggin in a jug
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together and store in the refrigerator. Drink 2 ounces a day.

title: minty melon bowl
directions: In salad bowl, combine all ingredients except jelly.
Melt jelly or stir with fork; pour over fruit.
Toss lightly.
Chill before serving.
If desired, garnish with fresh mint leaves.

title: marie's greek cookies(kouriembethes)
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy (about 15 minutes).
Add egg yolks, flavorings, almonds, soda, powder and cloves.
Mix until well blended.
Remove from beater and gradually add sifted flour to make a soft dough.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Place chicken breast in baking dish or pan.
Add water up to the sides of breast.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, sage and seasoning all over top.
Then spread uncooked Stove Top on top of chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: old fashioned lemon pie
directions: *For best results, use butter only.

title: pineapple velvet salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water.
Add the cream cheese and diced marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Chill until the gelatin begins to congeal.
Whip topping mix according to package directions.
Combine the topping with mayonnaise and fold into the gelatin mixture along with the pineapple and carrots.
Chill until firm.

title: cream cheese for bagels
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on hot toasted bagels.
Yields 8 servings (2 tablespoons each).
Keep this on hand for a filling bite on your way out the door in the mornings.
Has 50 calories. Fat free.

title: crusty eye of round
directions: Wipe eye of round with damp cloth. Make 4 knife slits and insert 1/2 clove garlic in each slit. Salt and sprinkle generously with freshly ground pepper. Flour generously. Criss-cross bacon strips and secure with toothpicks. Place roast on rack in shallow pan. Put bay leaf on bottom of pan under rack. Bake at 250° for 4 hours. Serves 6-8.

title: corn bread
directions: Empty meal in bowl.
Add the other ingredients, stirring well. Add milk only if mixture is not soft enough to pour.
Pour mixture into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° until well done (mixture starts to pull away from side of pan, or check with toothpick).
Let cool; cut into squares.
May be served cold or warm.

title: one dish rice and beef
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Stir in water, rice, onion, broth, garlic, mustard and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup cheese, bell pepper, and tomato. Simmer 10 more minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: super chocolate brownies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Beat in syrup, eggs and flour thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares (about 1 1/2 inches).
Makes 48 squares.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend eggs, oil, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add sugar and mix well.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Roll into ball and flatten between hands, approximately size of 50 cent piece.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar or with colored sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes and remove immediately.

title: beef soup
directions: Boil beef in water.
When it has come to a boil add salt, pepper, celery salt, onion and tomatoes.
Boil at least 2 hours.

title: welsh rabbit
directions: Melt fat in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat; stir in flour and add milk and salt.
Return to heat and stir until thick. Place over bottom part of double boiler; add cheese and mustard. When melted smoothly, serve.

title: honey bread pudding(how to use stale bread or biscuits)
directions: Toast bread cubes in oven for added flavor.
Place bread cubes in a small baking dish.
Combine the honey, butter or margarine, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Slowly stir in the milk.
Pour the mixture over the bread.
Sprinkle with the nutmeg.
Set the baking dish in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until pudding is set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bailey's irish cream(from guiness brewery, ireland)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Blend for 10 minutes with blender on high speed.
Refrigerate.
Shake well before using. Enjoy.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Brown meat, bell pepper and onion in oil.
Beat eggs, add milk, corn and other ingredients.
Sprinkle in corn meal slowly and mix together.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: savory vegetable drink
directions: In a 4-cup measure, stir together vegetable juice cocktail, Worcestershire sauce, dried marjoram and dried thyme.
Microwave, covered, on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until heated through.
Pour into 4 heatproof mugs.
Serve with celery stalk stirrers.

title: dilly butter garlic sauce
directions: Fry garlic in 1 Tbsp. butter, being careful not to burn garlic. Add rest of butter and dill.
Melt butter and remove from heat. Add lemon juice.
Use on Shishkabob with shrimp, chicken, potatoes, green pepper, onion, tomatoes, etc.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Add sugar to jello while still hot, then let cool.
Mix all together and refrigerate. Can use celery and nuts, but keeps longer by leaving these out.

title: fried bread
directions: Combine flour, whole wheat flour and salt in bowl.
Mix in shortening with fingers.
Stir in water with fork until mixture forms dough.
Shape into ball.
Let rest for 30 minutes. Knead on floured surface for 5 minutes or until smooth.
Roll 1/8-inch thick and cut in 3-inch circles.
Deep fry a few at a time in 365° oil for 30 seconds or until puffed.
Turn and fry 1 minute longer. Drain on paper towel.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Melt butter and work together with flour and cheese.
Roll and cut into rounds, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all and bake at 400° for 20 minutes; then turn oven down to 325° and bake for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cranapple-walnut cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar (or honey).
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour and dry ingredients.
Add to wet ingredients.
Stir.
Stir in apples, cranberries and nuts. Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: tea syrup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add tea leaves and simmer 5 minutes. Drain over sugar.
Stir to dissolve.
Keep refrigerated.
Dilute 1 part syrup to 7 parts water.

title: spinge(italian fritters)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add flour and baking powder.
Blend until smooth.
Drop by tablespoon into deep hot oil.
Fry until golden and cooked through.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm.

title: corn fritters
directions: If using fresh corn, cut tips from kernels with sharp knife and scrape cobs with dull edge of knife.
Add eggs, cracker crumbs and flour, sifted with baking powder, salt and pepper.
Drop from teaspoon into 1 1/2-inch of salad oil hot enough to brown bread cubes in 40 seconds.
Turn once.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen fritters.

title: sausage and cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet, or freeze and bake when needed.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cream cheese chews
directions: Cream
cake
mix,
butter and egg until smooth.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: farmer's market vegetables
directions: Heat oil in a heavy bottomed skillet and saute the onion and garlic over medium-low heat until tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the peppers; saute for 5 more minutes.
Add tomatoes and herbs.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cranberry stuffing balls
directions: In skillet, cook sausage, celery and onion until sausage is done.
Drain.
In a large bowl, combine meat mixture with remaining ingredients and enough broth to hold mixture together. Shape into 10 to 12 balls.
Place in a greased shallow baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Throw everything in a Dutch oven and stir.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes and stir 1/2 way through cooking.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth and creamy. Chill 2 hours or overnight is even better.
Contains 13 calories per teaspoon.

title: three hour beef stew
directions: Place cubed beef in bottom of baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Put cubed onions, carrots, celery and potatoes over meat. Sprinkle frozen peas over vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste. Top with can of tomato soup and can of water.
Cover tightly with foil.
Place in oven for 3 hours at 250°.
Do not open until served.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cocktail sauce. Place in freezer long enough to allow dip to become firm. Spread onto plate and cover with Cocktail sauce. Chill for 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to package.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together, then mix cheese mixture with Dream Whip.
Cut cake into bite size pieces.
Put half of cake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Put half of whip mixture on cake and repeat once more.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: trailblazer mix
directions: Brown meat; dump in rest of ingredients.
Stir.

title: betsy's best broccoli casserole
directions: Mix eggs, onion, mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Add drained broccoli.
Pour in baking dish and top with bread crumbs or crushed cheese Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: phoebe's smothered chicken
directions: Pound the chicken cutlets between 2 pieces of wax paper to thin, if they are thick.
Dredge chicken cutlets in the salt, pepper, thyme and flour.

Fry the onion in oil and remove. Brown coated chicken in oil and remove. Add some coating mix to the pan drippings, stir, then add the water, milk and bouillon cubes. Stir until thickened. Replace chicken and onion back in pan. Cover and cook on simmer until tender (20 or 25 minutes).

title: bible school pizza
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Spread pizza sauce on top of hamburger bun.
Put 1 or 2 tablespoons of browned meat and onion mixture on top of sauce.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of cheese on top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put raw rice in bottom of 9-inch casserole.
Add mushroom soup and cream of celery soup, diluted with water.
Add diced celery and sliced mushrooms; mix.
Skin and split chicken breasts.
Salt and pepper.
Place in casserole; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine in blender and process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator up to 1 week.

title: glazed fruit dessert
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple juice.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: stephanie's favorite quick and easy tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add tuna and soup.
Cook until desired temperature.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour, seasonings and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Stir over heat until melted.
Serve at once.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Boil water, chuck roast, onion, salt and pepper 1 hour gently. Add the next 6 ingredients.
Cook until tender, then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when serving.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Saute hamburger, pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and barbecue sauce.
Simmer slow (can be used in crock-pot).
Lima beans are the only ones that need to be drained.

title: blender pie
directions: Put everything in a blender.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered deep pie dish.
Bake at 400° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve cold.

title: sausage balls(appetizer)
directions: Add stuffing, oleo and water mixture and egg to sausage. Shape into small balls, then wrap 1/2 strip of bacon around each ball.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Fry okra in the oil on medium heat until the okra is no longer slimy.
Add chopped onion and cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and cook 3 minutes.
Add peeled shrimp and stir for 1 minute.
Add 3 quarts of water (more or less) and crab meat.
Stir to mix.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down to simmer until shrimp is done (about 20 minutes).
Serve over rice.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Into a 3-quart casserole, break apart the ground beef and add onion and garlic salt.
Brown on high, covered, for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 15 minutes on high, stirring and turning once.
Let rest for 5 minutes.

title: rachel's favorite hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate; cool a little.
Add sugar, milk and Karo syrup.
Bring to a boil and keep stirring.
Boil for about 5 minutes over medium heat.
The longer it boils, the stiffer it will be when you use it over ice cream.

title: beef and rotini
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions.
Add green beans the last 6 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In same saucepan, combine soup, rotini mixture, onion powder and pepper. Over medium heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Bring 3 quarts of tomatoes to a boil and slowly simmer until reduced in half (about 2 hours). Stir often to prevent burning. Add the rest of the tomatoes and all other ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes. Makes 5 pints.

title: shrimp wheels
directions: Mix together well all ingredients.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles (press at perforations to seal rectangles).
Spread mixture on each rectangle.
Starting at short end, roll up each rectangle like jellyroll.
Slice each roll into 10 slices and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot. May reheat.

title: raw relish
directions: Sprinkle salt over vegetables.
Let sit overnight.
Next morning, rinse and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Put in hot jars and seal.
No cooking.

title: yogurt cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumber and onion slices in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over slices.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: bulldog reducing diet
directions: Brown meat in butter slightly.
Add other 3 ingredients. Stir.
Turn on low heat; cover and cook until done.

title: baby plum cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add oil and eggs one at a time, beating well until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Fold in baby food, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Turn in a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn out and glaze while hot, if desired.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with a mixture of 1 cup brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Pour the rest of the cake batter over this and swirl with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: peachee pie supreme
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, pudding, margarine, egg and milk in large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch pie plate.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix all together good by hand.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan, oiled and floured.
Or it will make 2 (9-inch) layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese icing with nuts and coconut.

title: fail proof pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar and salt together.
Then beat vinegar, egg and water together.
Mix in with other.
Freeze
for 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, flour, sugar, salt, juice and oleo.
Add milk and pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Pour in crust.

title: mary lee's pizza sauce(enough for 2 pizzas)
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Just before light brown, add minced garlic.
Add remaining ingredients except sugar.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Before placing on pizza crust, add sugar.

title: chicken creole
directions: Boil chicken. Save stock. Debone chicken. Make a roux. Add onions, bell pepper and tomato paste. Stir 10 minutes over medium heat. Add 2 cups chicken stock and 1 cup water. Add salt and pepper. Add chicken and cook slowly for 30 minutes. Serve over rice. Serves 8 to 10.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cream cheese, condensed milk and pineapple.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Serve with various cut up fresh fruits.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and shape into a big ball.
Roll ball in chili powder.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: pistachio cookies
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk and mix.
Then add all dry ingredients and nuts or raisins; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
These burn easily so watch closely.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: world's best cream of broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli in chicken broth about 10 minutes or until tender.
Puree broth and broccoli in blender.
Mix half and half, milk, cheese and flour in blender.
Mix together broccoli and broth mixture with milk and cheese mixture.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens.
Serve with croutons and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well.
Hollow out a loaf of Hawaiian bread.
Break scooped out bread into pieces and toast.
Fill hollowed bread loaf with dip and serve with toasted pieces of bread.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Mix all ingredients together in 2-quart casserole.
Bake slow in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef. Add spaghetti mix and tomato sauce. Put mixture in bottom of oblong pan. Cover with Mozzarella cheese. Mushrooms and peppers are optional. Spoon sour cream around on top. Use crescent rolls to make crust on top. Spread butter and Parmesan cheese on top of rolls.
Bake in 375° oven until brown.

title: browned wild rabbit with gravy
directions: Place rabbit in pot; cover with water.
Add onion and bacon slices.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Add salt, if needed.
Cook rabbit until tender.
Remove from pot; drain. Place in hot skillet with small amount of cooking oil.
Brown quickly; place in a covered dish.
Keep warm.
Add salt, pepper, cornstarch, 1 1/2 cups water and a small amount of evaporated milk.
Serve gravy with rabbit.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine mustard and water. Allow to stand 10 minutes. Mix mustard, sugar, salt, paprika, onion powder and garlic salt with half of vinegar. Add oil gradually while beating with electric mixer. Add remaining vinegar and celery seed. Mix again. Yields about 1 1/2 cups. Great on green salad or making a dressing for pasta salad. Extra paprika adds a little more color.

title: chicken casserole 6
directions: Boil 1 chicken. Add extra water.
Cool and bone.
Combine bread crumbs, poultry seasoning and margarine.
In a casserole dish, layer crumbs, chicken, chicken soup, etc.
The top layer should be crumbs. Take broth from chicken and pour over mixture until moist.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mother's special devil's food cake
directions: Sift cake flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, cream of tartar and salt together.
Add sweet milk (*sour milk or buttermilk can be used and omit cream of tartar).
Beat for 2 minutes at number 3 speed.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes at number 3 speed. Pour into 2 greased 8-inch layer pans and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Chocolate Buttercream Frosting.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: coconut praline pie
directions: Mix frosting mix, butter and milk in saucepan. Heat over low heat until butter melts. Remove pan from heat. Put pecans in mixture; stir. Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust. Bake for 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: rice
directions: Soak rice in boiling water and salt for 1/2 hour; drain.
Fry rice in margarine until most of the margarine is gone.
Put rice in casserole with lid; sprinkle with garlic salt.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water; pour over rice.
Cover; bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Cook peaches and 1 cup sugar.
Melt butter in baking dish. Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour over melted butter. Pour cooked peaches over batter.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: yams and apples
directions: Boil yams in salted water; cool and peel.
Slice yams and apples alternately in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine and cook remaining ingredients until thickened.
Pour sauce over apples and yams.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, spices, salt, lemon juice and margarine. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is set in center. Cool.

title: sausage grits
directions: Cook sausage until brown in heavy skillet.
Drain well.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Combine grits, cheese and butter; stir until butter and cheese melt.
Combine eggs and milk; stir into grits.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield:
15 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In a large pot, lightly cook chicken in oil until the outside is white. Add onion, pepper, pineapple, Sloppy Joe sauce, sugar and vinegar.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes to one hour. Serve over rice.

title: chicken log
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Blend in next 3 ingredients and 2 tablespoons parsley flakes.
Shape mixture into a log.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Toss together the remaining parsley and almonds.
Coat log.
Serve with crackers.
Ideal for parties!!

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Wash and drain cranberries; mince (or grind) in blender or food processor.
Combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight. Add grapes, apple, walnuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream, just enough to moisten all ingredients. Transfer salad into serving bowl and garnish with holly, etc.
Freeze at least overnight (the salad will be served in the same bowl you freeze it in).
Let thaw 1 hour before serving.
It should be semi-frozen when served.
Freeze unused portion; refrigeration will not do!

title: pecan toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9x13 pan.
In large bowl combine cake mix and margarine; mix well with pastry blender or fork. Stir in egg to moisten.
Press mixture in bottom of greased pan. Bake at 350° for seven minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine the next 3 ingredients; spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked tomato and sauerkraut casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake in 325° oven for 2 1/4 hours.
This is a good accompaniment for pork or wild game.

title: pepper beef
directions: Slice beef thin; rinse, drain and season.
Saute slowly in butter; cover.
Slice green peppers.
Put sliced green peppers on top of the beef and cover.
Slice onions; put on top of beef and green pepper.
Cover and let cook slowly until meat is brown. Combine mushroom soup and beef gravy.
Stir into meat and continue to simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over plain or beef flavored rice.

title: chocolate cream pie(microwave)
directions: Mix the sugar, salt, cornstarch and cocoa, then add the milk. Cook on High until thick (5 to 6 minutes).
Add egg yolks; cook another minute or until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat well and add flavoring.
Bake at 325° in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl following directions on cake mix box. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Top with toasted coconut, if desired. Serves 12.

title: award winning chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using a spoon, stir eggs with sugar and vanilla; add butter.
Sift chocolate with flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture; add nuts.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes (optional).
Slice into French fry cuts.
Line 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with aluminum foil.
Put potatoes in; top with salt and pepper and other ingredients to taste.
Drip margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: breakfast tortilla
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place tortilla flat on baking sheet. Sprinkle grated cheese around edge of tortilla.
Crack egg in middle of tortilla.
Place in heated oven for 5 minutes.

title: refreshing summer drink
directions: Place apricots in blender and puree.
Serve with a dollop of whipped topping.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Optional: Any over veggies - mushrooms, green or yellow bell pepper, tomato, asparagus, etc.

title: teriyaki wings and brown rice
directions: Mix rice, butter, beef broth and bouillon cube and cook over medium heat, stirring until done.
Put wings in teriyaki sauce overnight with onion and seasoned salt, then put in oven at 350° until brown.
Put cooked rice in dish and add wings on top.

title: beef and potato loaf(juicy meat loaf bakes right over sliced potatoes.)
directions: Arrange potatoes, onion (sprinkled with salt, pepper and parsley flakes) evenly in greased 2-quart baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and spread this mixture evenly over the potatoes. Decorate top with more catsup, if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until potatoes are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Fry onions in butter until golden brown.
Combine meat with fried onions, bread crumbs, eggs, salt, pepper, sugar and nutmeg. Roll into one-inch balls and fry in butter or oil until brown. Shake ball soften to keep round.
Remove balls and add flour and blend.
Add bouillon and milk or cream and stir until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Add meat balls, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: wild strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix margarine and brown sugar until creamy.
Add crushed pretzels (not too fine).
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add very cold strawberries (can use 1 pound frozen strawberries).
Cool until it begins to set.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup white sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
When jello begins to set, put it over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream southern pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Combine cake flour and baking soda; add to butter mixture, one cup at a time.
(Batter will be thick.) Add egg yolks to batter and mix well.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in beaten egg whites.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool completely.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour mixture of all ingredients except bread and oleo into greased baking dish.
Top with cubed bread with oleo melted over. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Very good served with poultry or pork.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of a baking pan with 1/2 of Doritos chips.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of Doritos.
Pour cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes over the chicken.
Cook about 25 minutes at 350°; then take out of oven.
Crush rest of Doritos and add these.
Grate cheese on top of casserole.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: In large bowl, beat together margarine and cream cheese.
Stir in the kernel corn, cream-style corn and onion.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from the oven; stir in half of the fried onions.
Sprinkle remaining fried onions on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Cook potato with peeling until tender.
Peel, mash and mix with sugar, less 4 tablespoons.
Roll out with this remaining sugar on pastry sheet.
(You may need more 10x sugar.)
Spread with peanut butter; roll and slice.
A little food coloring can be used for different holiday colors.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix melted butter with graham cracker crumbs.
Put crumbs in bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
Layer Eagle Brand milk, coconut and chocolate chips over crumbs.
Bake on 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in container.
Use 1/3 cup mixture to hot water for a cup of hot cocoa.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: *For hot enchiladas use Ro-Tel and hot sauce. For mild enchiladas, use tomatoes and mild sauce.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix everything together but potatoes.
Pour hash browns in rectangular baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Top wit corn flake crumbs mixed with a little margarine.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in bowl as follows:
Lettuce, 1/4 cup onion, 1/2 cup celery, green pepper, carrots, 1 cup peas and some cheese; repeat. Then spread Miracle Whip in which you have added celery seed. Place some cheese on top.
Place in refrigerator.

title: cheese cookies with filling
directions: Filling: Use preserves (apricot, peach, etc.).
Or:

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
You can use your own pizza sauce, then omit oregano and tomato paste.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat out in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs.
Add sugar and remaining margarine.
Beat until thick. (If necessary, add 1 cup of sugar.) Spread over crumb mixture.
Slice bananas lengthwise and lay
on top. Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts and arrange cherries on top.
Chill for several hours. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
according
to package directions; drain well and
place
in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish which has been sprayed with
Pam.
Melt
the
stick of margarine with the cheese. Pour
over the broccoli.
Mix the 1/2 stick of melted margarine with
the
cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over broccoli. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into balls and chill again.
Next, cook together the last 2 ingredients in a heavy pan until melted.
Dip balls in chocolate or butterscotch with a toothpick and lay on waxed paper.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup and vegetables together.
Microwave pie crusts 30 seconds to soften.
Place one crust in a 10-inch pie plate and fill with chicken mixture. Top with remaining crust. Crimp and make slits.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.
Enjoy.

title: squash casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Slice squash and onion into very thin rounds.
Layer in a casserole dish in the following order: Squash, onion, several pats of margarine, salt and pepper and cheese.
Repeat to make another layer.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: frozen punch
directions: Bring to boil sugar and water for 3 to 4 minutes. Then add orange, lemon and pineapple juices. Freeze. Thaw about 2 hours, then add ginger ale or 7-Up. Makes a slush. Serves 24 to 25.

title: english toffee
directions: Cover bottom of an 8 x 12-inch pan with foil that has been buttered.
In pan, sprinkle half of nuts, then half of the chocolate.
Bring butter, sugar, water and salt to a boil.
Boil to 300°.
Pour mixture over chocolate layer in pan and let cool slightly.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate on top, then sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Press lightly with back of spoon. Refrigerate.
When hard, break into pieces.

title: baked carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in buttered casserole.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 45 minutes longer.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers or squash and onion in pan with good bit of salt; pour boiling water to cover and let stand 1 hour.
Pour off water, then add spices, sugar and vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes after starts to boil, then place in jars and seal.

title: low calorie cabbage stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot and heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer until all vegetables are cooked and tender. Makes 10 servings of 2 cups each.

title: shrimp - crab
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into shallow casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8.
